2118    public boolean isFloorTradeDeleteRequestInSuceededCache(int productKey, CboeIdStruct tradeId, ExchangeAcronymStruct userAcronym, ExchangeFirmStruct userFirm)
2119    {
2120        String key = productKey + userAcronym.acronym + userFirm.firmNumber;
2121        CboeIdStruct recordedTtradeId = succeededFloorTradeDeletesCache.get(key);
2122        if(recordedTtradeId != null && recordedTtradeId.highCboeId == tradeId.highCboeId && recordedTtradeId.lowCboeId == tradeId.lowCboeId)
2123        {
2124            return true;
2125        }
2126        return false;
2127    }
2128    /**
2129     * Delete an entire trade. This method is meant to delete the full quantity of each and every
2130     * one of the parties (atomic trades) constituting a trade. It's original purpose is to handle
2131     * the deletion of handheld trades.
2132     * 
2133     * @param tradingSessionName The trading session name
2134     * @param productKey traded product
2135     * @param tradeId the trade id of the trade to delete
2136     * @param reasonDescription A text description of the reason the bust was performed
2137     * @throws SystemException
2138     * @throws CommunicationException
2139     * @throws AuthorizationException
2140     * @throws DataValidationException
2141     * @throws NotAcceptedException
2142     * @throws TransactionFailedException
2143     * @throws NotFoundException
2144     * 
2145     * @author Francisco Ojeda
2146     */
2147    private void deleteTrade(String tradingSessionName, int productKey, CboeIdStruct tradeId,
2148            ExchangeAcronymStruct userAcronym, ExchangeFirmStruct userFirm, String reasonDescription)
2149            throws SystemException, CommunicationException, AuthorizationException,
2150            DataValidationException, NotAcceptedException, TransactionFailedException,
2151            NotFoundException
2152    {
2153        if(Log.isDebugOn())
2154    {
2155        Log.debug(this, "In " + getClass().getName() + ".deleteTrade() ");
2156        }
2157 
2158        TradeReport tradeReport;
2159        
2160        //Validate tradeId, get TradeReportStruct and TradeReport for this trade
2161        try
2162        {
2163            tradeReport = getTradeReport(CboeId.longValue(tradeId));
2164        }
2165        catch (NotFoundException nfe)
2166        {
2167            throw ExceptionBuilder.notFoundException("Unable to find trade report "
2168                    + "for tradeId: " + tradeId.highCboeId + " " + tradeId.lowCboeId, 0);
2169        }
2170 
2171        // Validate trade source
2172        if (tradeReport.getTradeSource().equals(TradeSources.SYSTEM))
2173        {
2174            throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(
2175                    "Busts for trades with source system are not allowed. Invalid trade souce "
2176                            + "for trade with tradeId: " + tradeId.highCboeId + " "
2177                            + tradeId.lowCboeId, DataValidationCodes.INVALID_TRADE_SOURCE);
2178            }
2179 
2180        // Validate productKey
2181        if( productKey != tradeReport.getProduct() )
2182        {
2183            String message = "Product key " + productKey + " does not match trade's product key "
2184                    + tradeReport.getProduct() + " for trade with tradeId: " + tradeId.highCboeId
2185                    + " " + tradeId.lowCboeId;
2186            throw ExceptionBuilder.notAcceptedException(message, NotAcceptedCodes.INVALID_REQUEST);            
2187        }
2188        
2189        // Validate acronym presence 
2190        if( userAcronym == null ) 
2191        {
2192            String message = "Invalid userAcronym: user acronym cannot be null. "; 
2193            throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(message,
2194                    DataValidationCodes.INVALID_EXECUTING_BROKER);
2195        }
2196        
2197        if (userAcronym.exchange == null || userAcronym.exchange.length() <= 0 || 
2198            userAcronym.acronym == null || userAcronym.acronym.length() <= 0)
2199        {
2200            String message = "Invalid userAcronym: user acronym cannot contain null or empty values" +
2201            " userAcronym.exchange: " + userAcronym.exchange +
2202            ", userAcronym.acronym: " + userAcronym.acronym;
2203            throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(message,
2204                    DataValidationCodes.INVALID_EXECUTING_BROKER);
2205        }        
2206 
2207        // Validate firm presence
2208        if (userFirm == null)
2209        {
2210            String message = "Invalid userFirm: user firm cannot be null. ";
2211            throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(message,
2212                    DataValidationCodes.INVALID_EXECUTING_BROKER_FIRM);
2213        }
2214        
2215        if (userFirm.exchange == null || userFirm.exchange.length() <= 0 || 
2216            userFirm.firmNumber == null || userFirm.firmNumber.length() <= 0)
2217        {
2218            String message = "Invalid userFirm: user firm cannot contain null or empty values" +
2219            " userFirm.exchange: " + userFirm.exchange +
2220            ", userFirm.firmNumber: " + userFirm.firmNumber;
2221            throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(message,
2222                    DataValidationCodes.INVALID_EXECUTING_BROKER_FIRM);
2223        }        
2224        
2225        // Verify that it is not duplicated request.
2226        if(isFloorTradeDeleteRequestInSuceededCache(productKey, tradeId, userAcronym, userFirm))
2227        {
2228            String message = "Duplicated request: user attempted to delete an already deleted trade with tradeId: " 
2229                    + tradeId.highCboeId + " " + tradeId.lowCboeId;
2230            throw ExceptionBuilder.notAcceptedException(message, NotAcceptedCodes.INVALID_REQUEST);           
2231        }
2232 
2233        ExchangeAcronymContainer userAcronymContainer = new ExchangeAcronymContainer(userAcronym);
2234 
2235        // Get the number of trades to delete and if trade is PAR trade, it also determines if a
2236        // market maker requested the delete.
2237        int numOfTradesToDelBuyer = 0;
2238        int numOfTradesToDelSeller = 0;
2239        int numOfTradesToDel = 0;
2240        char marketMakerSide = Sides.UNSPECIFIED;
2241        boolean isMarketMakerRequestedDelete = false; // tells if delete is requested by the market
2242                                                      // maker. This is needed for PAR trades only.
2243        TradeReportEntry[] tradeReportEntries = tradeReport.getEntries(true);
2244        for (int i = 0; i < tradeReportEntries.length; ++i)
2245        {
2246            ExchangeAcronymContainer buyerBrokerContainer = new ExchangeAcronymContainer(
2247                    tradeReportEntries[i].getBuyer());
2248            ExchangeAcronymContainer sellerBrokerContainer = new ExchangeAcronymContainer(
2249                    tradeReportEntries[i].getSeller());
2250 
2251            if(Log.isDebugOn())
2252            {
2253                String message = "In " + getClass().getName() + ".deleteTrade()"
2254                        + " passed user acronym: " + userAcronymContainer
2255                        + " tradeReportEntry buyer broker: " + buyerBrokerContainer
2256                        + " tradeReportEntry seller broker: " + sellerBrokerContainer;
2257                Log.debug(this, message);
2258            }
2259            
2260            if (buyerBrokerContainer.equalsIgnoringExchange(userAcronymContainer))
2261            {
2262                marketMakerSide = getMarketMakerSide(tradeId, tradeReportEntries[i], tradeReport
2263                        .getTradeType(), Sides.BUY);
2264                ++numOfTradesToDelBuyer;
2265            }
2266            else if (sellerBrokerContainer.equalsIgnoringExchange(userAcronymContainer))
2267            {
2268                marketMakerSide = getMarketMakerSide(tradeId, tradeReportEntries[i], tradeReport
2269                        .getTradeType(), Sides.SELL);
2270                ++numOfTradesToDelSeller;
2271            }
2272        }
2273 
2274        if( numOfTradesToDelBuyer == 0 && numOfTradesToDelSeller == 0 ) 
2275        {
2276            String message = "User acronym mismatch. User acronym "
2277                    + userAcronymContainer.getAcronym()
2278                    + " does not match any acronym inside trade report with" + " tradeId: "
2279                    + tradeId.highCboeId + " " + tradeId.lowCboeId;
2280            throw ExceptionBuilder.notAcceptedException(message, NotAcceptedCodes.INVALID_REQUEST);                
2281        }
2282        
2283        if (numOfTradesToDelBuyer > numOfTradesToDelSeller)
2284        {
2285            numOfTradesToDel = numOfTradesToDelBuyer;
2286            isMarketMakerRequestedDelete = tradeReport.getTradeType() == TradeTypes.PAR_TRADE
2287                    && marketMakerSide == Sides.BUY;
2288            
2289            if(Log.isDebugOn())
2290            {
2291                String msg1 = "In " + getClass().getName() + " will delete " + Sides.BUY
2292                        + " side trades, numOfTradesToDel = " + numOfTradesToDel
2293                        + ", isMarketMakerRequestedDelete = " + isMarketMakerRequestedDelete;
2294                Log.debug(this, msg1);
2295            }
2296        }
2297        else if (numOfTradesToDelBuyer < numOfTradesToDelSeller)
2298        {
2299            numOfTradesToDel = numOfTradesToDelSeller;
2300            isMarketMakerRequestedDelete = tradeReport.getTradeType() == TradeTypes.PAR_TRADE
2301                    && marketMakerSide == Sides.SELL;
2302            if(Log.isDebugOn())
2303            {
2304                String msg1 = "In " + getClass().getName() + " will delete " + Sides.SELL
2305                        + " side trades, numOfTradesToDel = " + numOfTradesToDel
2306                        + ", isMarketMakerRequestedDelete = " + isMarketMakerRequestedDelete;
2307                Log.debug(this, msg1);
2308            }
2309        }
2310            
2311 
2312        // Generate the list of trades to delete
2313        if (numOfTradesToDel > 0)
2314        {
2315            BustTradeStruct[] tradesToDel = new BustTradeStruct[numOfTradesToDel];
2316            int j = 0;
2317            for ( int i = 0; i < tradeReportEntries.length; ++i )
2318            {
2319                if ((numOfTradesToDelBuyer > 0 && new ExchangeAcronymContainer(
2320                        tradeReportEntries[i].getBuyer())
2321                        .equalsIgnoringExchange(userAcronymContainer))
2322                        || (numOfTradesToDelSeller > 0 && new ExchangeAcronymContainer(
2323                                tradeReportEntries[i].getSeller())
2324                                .equalsIgnoringExchange(userAcronymContainer)))
2325                {
2326                    // This validation is just a precaution against a potential buffer overflow
2327                    // (array out of bounds) exception.
2328                    // Although not likely to happen the fact of dealing with two independent
2329                    // indexes (i & j) makes this
2330                    // a situation to prevent against of.
2331                    if( j > numOfTradesToDel )
2332                    {
2333                        String message = "Error computing the number of trades for trade report with"
2334                                + " tradeId: "
2335                                + tradeId.highCboeId
2336                                + " "
2337                                + tradeId.lowCboeId
2338                                + ". No trades were deleted.";
2339                        throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(message,
2340                                DataValidationCodes.INVALID_LIMITS);
2341                    }                              
2342 
2343                    BustTradeStruct tradeToDel = new BustTradeStruct();
2344                    tradeToDel.atomicTradeId = CboeId.toStruct(tradeReportEntries[i]
2345                            .getAtomicTradeId());
2346                    tradeToDel.bustedQuantity = tradeReportEntries[i].getQuantity();
2347                    tradeToDel.buyerReinstateRequested = false;
2348                    tradeToDel.sellerReinstateRequested = false;
2349                    tradesToDel[j] = tradeToDel;
2350                    ++j;
2351                } // end if
2352            }
2353                
2354            // Delete the list of trades to delete
2355            acceptTradeBustV2(tradingSessionName, productKey, tradeId, tradesToDel,
2356                    reasonDescription, isMarketMakerRequestedDelete, marketMakerSide);
2357            
2358            // At this point the delete trade request has been successful so it is add to the cache
2359            addToSucceededFloorTradeDeletesCache(productKey, tradeId, userAcronym, userFirm);
2360        }
2361        else
2362        {
2363            String message = "No trades inside trade report with " + " tradeId: "
2364                    + tradeId.highCboeId + " " + tradeId.lowCboeId + " matched user acronym: "
2365                    + userAcronymContainer + ". No trades were deleted.";
2366 
2367            Log.information(this, "In " + getClass().getName() + ".deleteTrade : " + message);
2368        }
2369    }

2371    /**
2372     * Returns the side the market maker is on (B or S) in a PAR trade. For all other trade types U
2373     * (UNSPECIFIED) is returned.
2374     * 
2375     * @param tradeId the trade id of the trade
2376     * @param tradeReportEntry report entry to analyze
2377     * @param tradeType trade type to act accordingly. 
2378     * @throws DataValidationException
2379     * @throws NotAcceptedException
2380     * 
2381     * @author Francisco Ojeda
2382     */    
2383    private char getMarketMakerSide(CboeIdStruct tradeId, TradeReportEntry tradeReportEntry,
2384            char tradeType, char side) throws DataValidationException, NotAcceptedException
2385    {
2386        char marketMakerSide = Sides.UNSPECIFIED; 
2387        if(tradeType == TradeTypes.PAR_TRADE)
2388        {
2389            String extensions = tradeReportEntry.getExtensions();   
2390            if(Log.isDebugOn())
2391            {
2392                Log.debug(this, "In " + getClass().getName()
2393                        + ".getMarketmakerSide(...) tradeReportEntry.getExtensions() = " + extensions);
2394            }
2395            
2396            ExtensionsHelper extensionsHelper;
2397            try
2398            {
2399                extensionsHelper =  new ExtensionsHelper(extensions);
2400                extensionsHelper.setFieldDelimiter(TradeReportEntryImpl.FIELD_VALUE_SEPARATOR);
2401            }
2402            catch(ParseException pe)
2403            {
2404                String msg = "Attempted to delete a PAR that has invalid extensions."
2405                        + " TradeId: " + tradeId.highCboeId + " " + tradeId.lowCboeId
2406                        + " extensions: " + extensions;
2407                throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(msg,
2408                        DataValidationCodes.INVALID_EXTENSIONS);
2409            }
2410 
2411            // Check that PAR trade was not deleted already. PAR trades already deleted contain the
2412            // OrigATId=... in the extensions field.
2413            String origATId = extensionsHelper
2414                    .getValue(TradeReportEntryImpl.ORIGINAL_ATOMIC_TRADE_ID);
2415            int indexOfOrigATId = extensions.indexOf(TradeReportEntryImpl.ORIGINAL_ATOMIC_TRADE_ID);
2416            if (origATId != null || (indexOfOrigATId >= 0))
2417            {
2418                String msg = "Attempted to delete a PAR trade that was already deleted."
2419                        + " TradeId: " + tradeId.highCboeId + " " + tradeId.lowCboeId
2420                        + " extensions: " + extensions;
2421                throw ExceptionBuilder.notAcceptedException(msg, NotAcceptedCodes.INVALID_REQUEST); 
2422            }
2423            
2424            // Get MM side by getting value of 'MMTN' from the extensions field.
2425            String mMSide = extensionsHelper.getValue(com.cboe.idl.constants.ExtensionFields.MMTN);
2426            if(mMSide != null)
2427            {
2428                if (mMSide.equals(com.cboe.idl.constants.ExtensionFields.BUY_SIDE))
2429                {
2430                    marketMakerSide = Sides.BUY;
2431                }
2432                else if (mMSide.equals(com.cboe.idl.constants.ExtensionFields.SELL_SIDE))
2433                {
2434                    marketMakerSide = Sides.SELL;
2435                }
2436            }
2437            else
2438            {
2439                String msg = "Attempted to delete a PAR trade that has no MM side in extensions."
2440                        + " TradeId: " + tradeId.highCboeId + " " + tradeId.lowCboeId
2441                        + " extensions: " + extensions;
2442                throw ExceptionBuilder.notAcceptedException(msg, NotAcceptedCodes.INVALID_REQUEST);
2443            }
2444            if(Log.isDebugOn())
2445            {
2446                Log.debug(this, "In " + getClass().getName() + " PAR trade with marketMakerSide = "
2447                        + marketMakerSide);
2448            }
2449        }   
2450        else if (tradeType == TradeTypes.HANDHELD_TRADE)
2451        {
2452            marketMakerSide = side;
2453        }
2454        return marketMakerSide;
2455    }

2802            List tieredPdpms = new ArrayList();
2803            String pdpms;

2812                    pdpms = pdpms.trim();
2813 
2814                    while (start < pdpms.length())
2815                    {
2816                        tieredPdpms.add(pdpms.substring(start, start + 3));
2817                        start += 3;
2818                    }
2819                }
2820            }
2821            catch (ParseException pe)
2822            {
2823            Log.alarm(this, "Extensions field parsing failed: " + extensions + " exception: " + pe);
2824            }
2825 
2826            return tieredPdpms;
2827        }

2946 
2947    /**
2948     * create atomic trades
2949     */
2950    protected int createAtomicTrades(ParticipantList biders, ParticipantList askers,
2951            ArrayList atomicTrades, TradingProduct product) throws DataValidationException
2952    {
2953        if (Log.isDebugOn())
2954        {
2955            Log.debug("TradeServiceImpl::createAtomicTrades >> invoqued for product (" + product + ") for ASYNC_TRADE or SYNC_TRADE");
2956        }          
2957        boolean isExceptionExit = true ;
2958        epCreateAtomicTrades.enter();
2959        try
2960        {
2961                Enumeration buyItems = biders.elements();
2962                Enumeration sellItems = askers.elements();
2963        if ((buyItems == null) || (sellItems == null))
2964        {
2965            isExceptionExit = false;
2966            return 0;
2967        }
2968        if ((!buyItems.hasMoreElements()) || (!sellItems.hasMoreElements()))
2969        { // initial checking
2970            isExceptionExit = false;
2971            return 0;
2972        }
2973        ParticipantItem buyer  = null;
2974        ParticipantItem seller = null;
2975        int buyQty   = 0;
2976        int sellQty  = 0;
2977        int matchQty = 0;
2978        int tradeQty = 0;
2979        while ((buyQty > 0 || buyItems.hasMoreElements())
2980                && (sellQty > 0 || sellItems.hasMoreElements()))
2981        {
2982            if (buyQty <= 0)
2983            {
2984                buyer = (ParticipantItem) buyItems.nextElement();
2985                buyQty = buyer.getParticipantQuantity();
2986                if (buyQty <= 0)
2987                {
2988                    Log.information("TradeServiceImpl.doTradeMatch>> participant item has no participant quantity::"+buyer);
2989                    continue;
2990                }
2991            }
2992            if (sellQty <= 0)
2993            {
2994                seller = (ParticipantItem) sellItems.nextElement();
2995                sellQty = seller.getParticipantQuantity();
2996                if (sellQty <= 0)
2997                {
2998                    Log.information("TradeServiceImpl.doTradeMatch>> participant item has no participant quantity::"+seller);
2999                    continue;
3000                }
3001            }
3002            tradeQty = (buyQty < sellQty)
3003                    ? buyQty
3004                    : sellQty;
3005            AtomicTrade atomicTrade = new AtomicTradeImpl(buyer, seller, tradeQty, product);
3006            atomicTrades.add(atomicTrade);
3007            buyQty   -= tradeQty;
3008            sellQty  -= tradeQty;
3009            matchQty += tradeQty; // keep track of the sum of all the individual AtomicTrades
3010        }
3011        isExceptionExit = false;
3012        if (Log.isDebugOn())
3013        {
3014            Log.debug("TSI.createAtomicTrades >> matchQty = " + matchQty + " for ASYNC_TRADE or SYNC_TRADE");
3015        }        
3016        return matchQty;
3017    }
3018        finally
3019        {
3020            epCreateAtomicTrades.exit(isExceptionExit);  
3021        }
3022         
3023      
3024   
3025    }
3026 
3027        /**
3028         * Will obtain a a TradeReport given a tradeId
3029         *
3030         * author Matt Sochacki
3031         *
3032         * @return TradeReportStruct
3033         */
3034    private TradeReport getTradeReport(long tradeId) throws NotFoundException, SystemException
3035    {
3036        TradeReport tradeReport;
3037 
3038        try
3039        {
3040            tradeReport = getTradeReportHome().findByKey(tradeId);
3041        }
3042        catch (TransactionFailedException pe)
3043        {
3044                        String msg = "Unable to retrieve TradeReport due to persistenceException, and going to throw SystemException";
3045            Log.exception(this, msg, pe);
3046            throw ExceptionBuilder.systemException(msg, 0);
3047                }
3048        if (tradeReport == null || !tradeReport.isReportForLocalTradeServer())
3049        {
3050            Log.information(this, "Dismissing the found trade report with trade id " + tradeId

3505                            updateTradables(tradingProduct.getProductKey(), buyParticipants, sellParticipants, tradePrice, ctCommand);
3506                            updateOrderBook(true, null, tradingProduct, buyParticipants, sellParticipants);

3509                        {

3511                        }

3513                                    //CreateSpreadTradeCommand ctCommand =  CreateSpreadTradeCommand.getInstance();

3515                                                    null, buyParticipants, legBuyParticipants, sellParticipants, legSellParticipants, tradePrice, tradePrices, derivedTradeSide, legPrices);
3516                                    ctCommand.setEmitPointContext(epTradeMatch.makeCopyOfThreadContext());
3517                    }
3518                        else
3519                        {

3521                            ctCommand.capturePriorTradeData(buyParticipants,  sellParticipants);
3522

3524                     updateOrderBook(true, null, tradingProduct, buyParticipants, sellParticipants);

3528                     }                     
3529                     //CreateTradeCommand ctCommand = CreateTradeCommand.getInstance();

3532                        }
3533                        }
3534                        else
3535                        {

3537                report.completeTrade(true, null, true);
3538                        }
3539        }

3542    /**
3543         *  Creates a trade for the cross
3544     * 
3545         *  @param aCross - the cross to be executed
3546     *  @exception DataValidationException if the cross is for an unknown product.
3547         */
3548    public void createCrossTrade(Cross aCross, Price tradingPrice, OrderBook book)
3549            throws SpreadProcessingException, DataValidationException, SystemException
3550    {
3551        Order buyOrder = aCross.getBuyOrder();
3552        Order sellOrder = aCross.getSellOrder();
3553 
3554        int tradeQuantity = Math.min(buyOrder.getQuantityAllowed(), sellOrder.getQuantityAllowed());
3555 
3556        if (tradeQuantity > 0)
3557        {
3558            boolean isLinkedAwayTradeAndBuySideIsLinkedAway = false;
3559            boolean isLinkedAwayTradeAndSellSideIsLinkedAway = false;
3560            try
3561            {
3562                isLinkedAwayTradeAndBuySideIsLinkedAway = aCross.isCrossWithAutoLinkedPAOrder()
3563                        && aCross.isLinkedAwaySideABuy();
3564                isLinkedAwayTradeAndSellSideIsLinkedAway = aCross.isCrossWithAutoLinkedPAOrder()
3565                        && (!aCross.isLinkedAwaySideABuy());
3566            }
3567            catch (NotSupportedException e)
3568            {
3569                // ignore, which means the cross does not support link away; keep default FALSE for
3570                // both
3571            }
3572 
3573            ParticipantList buyList = new ParticipantListImpl();
3574            ParticipantItem buyer = new ParticipantItemImpl(buyOrder, tradeQuantity,
3575                    isLinkedAwayTradeAndBuySideIsLinkedAway
3576                            ? ParticipantItem.LINKED_AWAY
3577                            : ParticipantItem.NONE);
3578            buyList.addElement(buyer);
3579 
3580            ParticipantList sellList = new ParticipantListImpl();
3581            ParticipantItem seller = new ParticipantItemImpl(sellOrder, tradeQuantity,
3582                    isLinkedAwayTradeAndSellSideIsLinkedAway
3583                            ? ParticipantItem.LINKED_AWAY
3584                            : ParticipantItem.NONE);
3585            sellList.addElement(seller);
3586 
3587            char tradeTypeToUse = getTradeType(aCross, book);
3588 
3589            if(isAsynchronousTradingEnabled(book.getTradingProduct()))
3590            {
3591                    
3592                    if (book.getTradingProduct().isStrategy())
3593                    {     
3594                            Side derivedTradeSide = null;
3595                    StrategyLegTradePrice[] legPrices = null;
3596                    legPrices = getLegPrices(book.getTradingProduct(), buyList, sellList, tradingPrice, false, false);
3597                    derivedTradeSide = getDerivedTradeSide(buyList, sellList);
3598                    
3599                    ParticipantList[] legBuyParticipants;
3600                    ParticipantList[] legSellParticipants;
3601                    legBuyParticipants = buyList.getListsForLegs(legPrices, derivedTradeSide, null);
3602                    legSellParticipants = sellList.getListsForLegs(legPrices, derivedTradeSide, null);
3603                    
3604                    //get trade prices, sides and products
3605                    Price[] tradePrices = getTradePricesFrom(legPrices);                                      
3606                    Side[] legSides = getLegSidesFrom(legPrices);
3607                    TradingProduct[] tradingProducts = getTradingProductsFrom(legPrices);
3608                    
3609                    CreateSpreadTradeCommand ctCommand = CreateSpreadTradeCommand.getInstance();
3610                    ctCommand.capturePriorTradeData(buyList, legBuyParticipants, sellList, legSellParticipants);
3611                    
3612                    
3613                    for (int i = 0; i < tradePrices.length; i++)
3614                    {
3615                        updateTradables(legPrices[i].getProductKey(),legBuyParticipants[i],legSellParticipants[i],tradePrices[i], ctCommand);
3616 
3617                        if(tradingProducts[i] != null)
3618                        {
3619                            updateOrderBook(true, null, tradingProducts[i], 
3620                                            legSides[i].isBuySide() ? legBuyParticipants[i] : legSellParticipants[i], 
3621                                            legSides[i].isBuySide() ? legSellParticipants[i] : legBuyParticipants[i]);
3622                        }
3623                    }                   
3624                                        
3625                                    updateTradables(book.getTradingProduct().getProductKey(), buyList, sellList, tradingPrice, ctCommand);
3626                        updateOrderBook(true, null, book.getTradingProduct(), buyList, sellList);
3627                        
3628                        if (Log.isDebugOn())
3629                        {
3630                            Log.debug("TradeServiceImpl::createCrossTrade>> creating CreateSpreadTradeCommand for ASYNC_TRADE");
3631                        }
3632                        
3633                                    //CreateSpreadTradeCommand ctCommand =  CreateSpreadTradeCommand.getInstance();
3634                                    ctCommand.setContext(CreateSpreadTradeCommand.DO_TRADE_MATCH_FOR_SPREAD, book.getTradingProduct(),null,
3635                                                    null, buyList, legBuyParticipants, sellList, legSellParticipants, tradingPrice, tradePrices, derivedTradeSide, legPrices);
3636                                    ctCommand.setTradeType(tradeTypeToUse);
3637                                    ctCommand.setSettlementTradeType(getSettlementTradeType(aCross, book));
3638                                    ctCommand.setHeldOrderTrade(aCross.isProcessingOutOfSequence());
3639                                ctCommand.setEmitPointContext(epTradeMatch.makeCopyOfThreadContext());
3640                    }
3641                    else
3642                    {
3643                            CreateTradeCommand ctCommand =  CreateTradeCommand.getInstance();
3644                            ctCommand.capturePriorTradeData(buyList,  sellList);
3645                            
3646                            updateTradables( book.getTradingProduct().getProductKey(), buyList, sellList, tradingPrice, ctCommand);
3647                    
3648                    if (Log.isDebugOn())
3649                    {
3650                        Log.debug("TradeServiceImpl::createCrossTrade>> creating CreateTradeCommand for ASYNC_TRADE");
3651                    }                            
3652                            //CreateTradeCommand ctCommand =  CreateTradeCommand.getInstance();
3653                                        ctCommand.setContext( book.getTradingProduct(),  null,  buyList,  sellList, tradingPrice );
3654                                        ctCommand.setTradeType(tradeTypeToUse);
3655                                        ctCommand.setSettlementTradeType(getSettlementTradeType(aCross, book));
3656                                        ctCommand.setHeldOrderTrade(aCross.isProcessingOutOfSequence());
3657                                            ctCommand.setEmitPointContext(epTradeMatch.makeCopyOfThreadContext());
3658                }
3659                    
3660            }
3661            else
3662            {
3663            TradeReport report = tradeMatch(book.getTradingProduct(), tradeTypeToUse,
3664                        getSettlementTradeType(aCross, book), aCross.isProcessingOutOfSequence(),
3665                        buyList, sellList, tradingPrice, (TradeReport) null, null, false, false, false, null, new HashMap());
3666                    
3667                    report.completeTrade(false, null, true);
3668            }
3669        }
3670        else
3671        {
3672            Log.alarm(this, "createCrossTrade::trade quantity is 0.");
3673        }
3674    }

3707            {

3758                              ctCommand.setEmitPointContext(epTradeMatch.makeCopyOfThreadContext());

3917    /**
3918     * Creates a trade for the incoming spread with legs
3919     */
3920    public int createSpreadTradeWithLegs(Tradable aTradable, TradingProduct product,
3921            DerivedQuote derivedQuote) throws SpreadProcessingException, DataValidationException,
3922            SystemException
3923    {
3924        int tradeQuantity;
3925        int quantityInDerivedQ;
3926        Side tradableSide = aTradable.getSide();
3927        Price spreadSidePrice;

3929                .getStrategyLegTradeContainer(product, derivedQuote, aTradable);

4053    protected int tradeCrossProductLegs(Order strategyOrder, TradingProduct strategy,
4054            DerivedQuote derivedQuote, AuctionInternal auction) throws SystemException,
4055            DataValidationException
4056    {
4057        Broker broker = strategy.getBroker();
4058        Log.information("TradeServiceImpl::tradeCrossProductLegs >> Attempting leg trading on Order["+strategyOrder.toString()+"]...");
4059        ProcessStrategyLegsCommand cmd = StrategyTradeServiceHelper
4060                .createProcessStrategyLegsCommand(strategyOrder, broker, derivedQuote, strategy,
4061                        auction);
4062        try
4063        {  
4064            getClassBroker(strategy.getTradingClass().getProductClassKey()).acceptCommand(cmd,
4065                    false/* !ignoreQueueLimit ("execute now") */);
4066            cmd.waitForCompletion();  // (support possible asynchronous execution)
4067        }
4068        catch (Exception e)
4069        {
4070            Log
4071            .exception(
4072                    "TradeServiceImpl::tradeCrossProductLegs >> ProcessStrategyLegsCommand as a sub-command call failed, but proceed to the next step regardless",
4073                    e);
4074            return 0;
4075        }
4076        int qtyTraded = cmd.getSpreadTradeQuantity();
4077        if (qtyTraded == 0)
4078        {
4079            Log.information("TradeServiceImpl::tradeCrossProductLegs >> Attempted leg trading on Order[" + strategyOrder.toString()
4080                    + "] but NO TRADE");
4081        }
4082        else
4083        {
4084            Log.information("TradeServiceImpl::tradeCrossProductLegs >> Order[" + strategyOrder.toString() + "] leg trading filled qty="
4085                    + qtyTraded);
4086        }
4087        
4088        if (Log.isDebugOn())
4089        {
4090            Log.debug("TradeServiceImpl::tradeCrossProductLegs >> Order[" + strategyOrder.toString() + "] leg trading filled qty=" + qtyTraded + " for ASYNC_TRADE or SYNC_TRADE");
4091        }
4092        return qtyTraded;
4093    }

4097            SystemException
4098    {

4264 
4265    /*
4266     * This change for the specific case when an incoming DAIM Spread order changes the state of the
4267     * spread product from ON_HOLD to OPEN. In this case, the daim participants should be penalized.
4268     * But in the scenario where there is a resting DAIM spread order and a leg market change is
4269     * triggering the state change from ON_HOLD to OPEN, there should be no penalization since the
4270     * DAIM order has already booked.
4271         */
4272    protected Tradable getTradableForDAIMAllocation(OrderBook aBook, Side tradeSide)
4273    {
4274            Tradable tradable = null;
4275                OrderBookSideItem orderBookSideItem;                                  
4276                OrderBookImpl orderBook = null;
4277                if(aBook instanceof OrderBookImpl)
4278                        orderBook= (OrderBookImpl)aBook;                                  
4279 
4280                if(orderBook.getBuySideItem().getSide().isSameSide(tradeSide))
4281                {
4282                        orderBookSideItem = orderBook.getBuySideItem();
4283                }
4284                else
4285                {
4286                        orderBookSideItem = orderBook.getSellSideItem();
4287                 }
4288                  
4289                 if(orderBookSideItem.getFirstLimitPriceItem().getNextItem() == null)
4290                 {
4291            PriceDetailIterator iterator = orderBookSideItem.getFirstLimitPriceItem()
4292                    .getPriceDetails();
4293                          OrderBookPriceDetailImpl firstPriceDetail=null;
4294                          while(iterator!=null && iterator.hasNext())
4295                          {
4296                                        firstPriceDetail = (OrderBookPriceDetailImpl)iterator.next();
4297                                        if(!iterator.hasNext())
4298                                        {
4299                                                tradable = firstPriceDetail.getTradable();
4300                                                if( tradable instanceof OrderImpl)
4301                                                {
4302                        if (((OrderImpl) tradable).isDirectedAIMOrderMatched()
4303                                && ((OrderImpl) tradable).getDAIMedUserList() != null
4304                                && ((OrderImpl) tradable).getDAIMedUserList().size() > 0)
4305                                                        {
4306                                                                ((OrderImpl)tradable).setDirectedAIMOrderAndNotMatched(false);
4307                                                        }
4308                                                        else
4309                                                        {
4310                                                                tradable =null;
4311                                                        }
4312                                                }
4313                                                else
4314                                                {
4315                                                        tradable =null;
4316                                                }
4317                                        }
4318                          }
4319                  }
4320                 return tradable;
4321    }

4323    public List<Tradable> getPrioritizedTradables(Order anOrder, Side side, OrderBook book,
4324            Price endingPrice, boolean nonQTrade) throws SystemException, DataValidationException
4325    {
4326 
4327        Iterator sets;
4328        PriorityTradableSet nextSet;
4329        OrderBookPriceDetail priceDetail;
4330        List<Tradable> tradables = new ArrayList<Tradable>();
4331 
4332        AllocationTradeContextImpl allocationContext;
4333        allocationContext = new AllocationTradeContextImpl(AllocationTradeTypes.REGULAR);
4334        allocationContext.setNonQAllocation(nonQTrade);
4335        //DAIM change: Set the tradable in the allocation Context.
4336        if (!anOrder.isBookedByAuction())// The penalization should not take place if the order has
4337                                         // auctioned.
4338        {
4339                allocationContext.setTradable(((Tradable) anOrder));
4340        }
4341 
4342        List preferredFirmAcronym = getPreferredFirmAcronym(anOrder);
4343        int legRatio = calculateLegRatio(anOrder.getProductKey(), book.getTradingProduct()
4344                .getProductKey());
4345        if (preferredFirmAcronym != null && preferredFirmAcronym.size() != 0)
4346        {
4347            allocationContext.setPreferredFirm(preferredFirmAcronym);
4348            allocationContext.setQtyForPmmAllocation(anOrder.getQuantityAllowed()*legRatio);
4349        }
4350        
4351        sets = book.getPrioritySets(side, endingPrice, Integer.MAX_VALUE, allocationContext);
4352 
4353        while (sets.hasNext())

4530    private int createParticipantListsBasedOnKnownSide(int[] knownSideQtySplits,
4531            ArrayList outputParticipantList, ArrayList outputTradePrices,
4532            ArrayList outputTradeQuantityList, List preferredFirmAcronym,
4533            String preferredFirmExchange, TradingProduct aProduct, OrderBook book,
4534            Side tradableSide, Price endingPrice, int quantityToAllocate,
4535            boolean needsSingleFillOnly, Tradable tradable,AuctionInternal auction)
4536     {
4537        boolean nonQTrade = false;
4538                Tradable spreadTradable  = null;
4539                if(tradable instanceof SpreadTradableImpl)
4540                        spreadTradable = ((SpreadTradableImpl)tradable).getTradable();
4541 
4542            int allocatedQty = 0;
4543        if(auction != null)
4544        {
4545                allocatedQty = createParticipantListsForCPSCOA( outputParticipantList,
4546                    outputTradePrices, outputTradeQuantityList, preferredFirmAcronym,
4547                    preferredFirmExchange, aProduct, book, tradableSide, endingPrice,
4548                    quantityToAllocate, nonQTrade, needsSingleFillOnly, spreadTradable, auction);
4549        }
4550        //PMM-END
4551        else
4552        {
4553                allocatedQty = createParticipantLists(outputParticipantList, outputTradePrices,
4554                outputTradeQuantityList, preferredFirmAcronym, preferredFirmExchange, aProduct,
4555                book, tradableSide, endingPrice, quantityToAllocate, nonQTrade,
4556                    needsSingleFillOnly, false, spreadTradable, false);
4557        }
4558 
4559        if (knownSideQtySplits == null)
4560            return allocatedQty;
4561        // TODO: This is totally coupled with the cross product leg trading logic
4562        //      which supposely should always have 1-1 trading
4563        //      This special case should only happen on an attempt to trade
4564        //           at pre-determined multiple qty levels with a resting AON order
4565        //      Note, the code only attempts to work on this one condition
4566        //      This is in place when no better solution is available without massive code change
4567        //      2007/08/14
4568        int oppoSideSplits = outputParticipantList.size();
4569        if (allocatedQty == quantityToAllocate)
4570        {
4571            if (oppoSideSplits < knownSideQtySplits.length)
4572            {
4573                int j = 0;
4574                for (int i = 0; i < oppoSideSplits; i++)
4575                {
4576                    int cur = ((Integer) outputTradeQuantityList.get(i)).intValue();
4577                    if (cur > knownSideQtySplits[j])
4578                    {
4579                        outputParticipantList.add(i + 1, outputParticipantList.get(i));
4580                        outputTradePrices.add(i + 1, outputTradePrices.get(i));
4581                        outputTradeQuantityList.remove(i);
4582                        outputTradeQuantityList.add(i, new Integer(knownSideQtySplits[j]));
4583                        outputTradeQuantityList
4584                                .add(i + 1, new Integer(cur - knownSideQtySplits[j]));
4585                        oppoSideSplits += 1;
4586                        j += 1;
4587                    }
4588                    else if (cur == knownSideQtySplits[j])
4589                    {
4590                        continue;
4591                    }
4592                    else
4593                    {
4594                        Log.alarm("Allocation issue: expect to fill " + knownSideQtySplits[j]
4595                                + " at one price, but only got " + cur
4596                                + "; abort CP option leg trading");
4597                        return 0;
4598                    }
4599                }
4600                return allocatedQty;
4601            }
4602            else if (oppoSideSplits == knownSideQtySplits.length)
4603            {
4604                return allocatedQty;
4605            }
4606            else
4607            {
4608                Log.alarm("Allocation issue: expect to fill at " + knownSideQtySplits.length
4609                        + " price levels, but got " + oppoSideSplits);
4610                return 0;
4611            }
4612        }
4613        else
4614        {
4615            Log.alarm("Allocation issue: expect to fill " + quantityToAllocate + ", but only got "
4616                    + allocatedQty);
4617           return 0;
4618        }
4619    }

5042                            ctCommand.setTradeReportParam(tradeReportParam);

5045                    }

5066                }

5068            }
5069        }

5073 public void updateOrderBook(boolean updateOrderBook, Tradable unbookedTradable, TradingProduct tradingProduct, ParticipantList nextBuyList, ParticipantList nextSellList) throws DataValidationException
5074 {
5075         try
5076         {
5077          
5078             if(tradingProduct == null)
5079             {
5080                 return;
5081             }
5082             
5083             if (updateOrderBook)
5084             {
5085                     OrderBook book = tradingProduct.getOrderBook();
5086                     Side bidSide;
5087                     Side askSide;
5088                     if (tradingProduct.isStrategy()) {
5089                             bidSide = SideFactory.getAsDefinedSide();
5090                             askSide = SideFactory.getOppositeSide();
5091                     }
5092                     else {
5093                             bidSide = SideFactory.getBuySide();
5094                             askSide = SideFactory.getSellSide();
5095                     }
5096                     updateBookStructure(book, bidSide, nextBuyList, unbookedTradable);
5097                     updateBookStructure(book, askSide, nextSellList, unbookedTradable);
5098             }
5099     }
5100         catch(Exception ex)
5101         {
5102                 if (Log.isDebugOn())
5103             {
5104                         Log.debug(this, "TradeServiceImpl::updateOrderBook - Exception updating Orderbook " + ex);
5105             }
5106                 // rolling back the tradables for Async Trade
5107                 completeParticipantsTrade(nextBuyList);
5108                 completeParticipantsTrade(nextSellList);
5109                 
5110                 throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(
5111                 "Unable to update the Orderbook ", 0);                 
5112         }
5113}

5116private void completeParticipantsTrade(ParticipantList pList) {
5117        Enumeration thisParticipantEnum = pList.elements();

5119        {

5121                if(!nextParticipantItem.getParticipantTradable().isSkipUpdateForAsyncTrade())
5122                {
5123                        nextParticipantItem.getParticipantTradable().completeAsyncCreateTrade();
5124                }
5125        }

5203    /**
5204     * This method will create trade for the given tradable against the given list of tradables.
5205     * Assumptions:- All trades will be at one price, that will be price of tradable. Trade quantity
5206     * will be lesser of 'availabel qty' for tradable OR 'available qty' for all the tradables on
5207     * opposite side.
5208     *

5210     * satisfaction. OR B. Inbound Satisfaction Order.

5212     * satisfaction OR B. MM orders to be traded with inbound Satisfaction order.

5215     * @param needsBookUpdate - If order book needs to be updated or not.A. true for
5216     * customerOrderSatisfy B. false when inbound S order tradeWithCrowd
5217     * @return quantity traded
5218     * @throws SpreadProcessingException
5219     * @throws DataValidationException
5220     * @throws SystemException
5221     */
5222    public int createSatisfactionOrderTrade(Tradable tradable, Enumeration oppositeSideTradables,
5223            OrderBook book, int maxAllowedQuantity, boolean needsBookUpdate)
5224            throws SpreadProcessingException, DataValidationException, SystemException
5225    {
5226        if (Log.isDebugOn())
5227        {
5228            Log.debug(this, "Creating trade for Satisfaction order.");
5229        }
5230 
5231        ArrayList tradableSideList = new ArrayList();
5232        ArrayList oppositeSideList = new ArrayList();
5233        ArrayList priceList = new ArrayList();
5234        ArrayList quantities = new ArrayList();
5235        Side tradableSide;
5236        int tradeQuantity = 0;
5237 
5238        tradableSide = tradable.getSide();
5239 
5240        // Create Opposite side participant list.
5241        int oppositeSideQuantity = createParticipantListForSatisfaction(oppositeSideList,
5242                oppositeSideTradables, maxAllowedQuantity);
5243 
5244        tradeQuantity = (oppositeSideQuantity < maxAllowedQuantity)
5245                ? oppositeSideQuantity
5246                : maxAllowedQuantity;
5247 
5248        // Create tradableside Participant list
5249        ParticipantList tradableParticipantList = new ParticipantListImpl();
5250        createParticipantItem(tradable, tradeQuantity, tradableParticipantList);
5251        tradableSideList.add(tradableParticipantList);
5252 
5253        quantities.add(new Integer(tradeQuantity));
5254        priceList.add(tradable.getPrice());
5255 
5256        if (tradableSide.isBuySide())
5257        {
5258            completeSatisfactionTrades(tradable, tradableSideList, oppositeSideList, priceList,
5259                    quantities, book, tradableSide.getOtherSide()/* side to be updated */,
5260                    needsBookUpdate);
5261        }
5262        else
5263        {
5264            completeSatisfactionTrades(tradable, oppositeSideList, tradableSideList, priceList,
5265                    quantities, book, tradableSide.getOtherSide()/* side to be updated */,
5266                    needsBookUpdate);
5267        }
5268        return tradeQuantity;
5269    }

5271    /**
5272     *
5273     * @param unBookedTradable
5274     * @param buyLists
5275     * @param sellLists
5276     * @param prices
5277     * @param quantities
5278     * @param book
5279     * @param side
5280     * @throws SpreadProcessingException
5281     * @throws DataValidationException
5282     * @throws SystemException
5283     */
5284    protected void completeSatisfactionTrades(Tradable unBookedTradable, ArrayList buyLists,
5285            ArrayList sellLists, ArrayList prices, ArrayList quantities, OrderBook book, Side side,
5286            boolean needsBookUpdated) throws SpreadProcessingException, DataValidationException,
5287            SystemException
5288    {
5289        boolean isTBForCOB = false;//isTBForCOB(unBookedTradable);
5290       
5291        // first validate that both lists are same size
5292        int tradeCount = buyLists.size();
5293        if (sellLists.size() != tradeCount || prices.size() != tradeCount
5294                || quantities.size() != tradeCount)
5295        {
5296            throw new IllegalArgumentException("all ArrayLists must have same number of elements");
5297        }
5298 
5299        // now actually create the trades
5300        for (int i = 0; i < buyLists.size(); i++)
5301        {
5302            ParticipantList nextBuy = (ParticipantList) buyLists.get(i);
5303            ParticipantList nextSell = (ParticipantList) sellLists.get(i);
5304 
5305            Price tradePrice = (Price) prices.get(i);
5306 
5307            if(isAsynchronousTradingEnabled(book.getTradingProduct())) // async trade match
5308            {
5309                    if (book.getTradingProduct().isStrategy())
5310                    {   
5311                            Side derivedTradeSide = null;
5312                    StrategyLegTradePrice[] legPrices = null;
5313                    legPrices = getLegPrices(book.getTradingProduct(), nextBuy, nextSell, tradePrice, false, isTBForCOB);
5314                    derivedTradeSide = getDerivedTradeSide(nextBuy, nextSell);
5315                    
5316                    ParticipantList[] legBuyParticipants;
5317                    ParticipantList[] legSellParticipants;
5318                    legBuyParticipants = nextBuy.getListsForLegs(legPrices, derivedTradeSide, null);
5319                    legSellParticipants = nextSell.getListsForLegs(legPrices, derivedTradeSide, null);
5320                    
5321                    //get trade prices, sides and products
5322                    Price[] tradePrices = getTradePricesFrom(legPrices);
5323                    Side[] legSides = getLegSidesFrom(legPrices);
5324                    TradingProduct[] tradingProducts = getTradingProductsFrom(legPrices);
5325                    
5326                    CreateSpreadTradeCommand ctCommand = CreateSpreadTradeCommand.getInstance();
5327                    ctCommand.capturePriorTradeData(nextBuy, legBuyParticipants, nextSell, legSellParticipants);
5328                    
5329                    for (int j = 0; j < tradePrices.length; j++)
5330                    {
5331                        updateTradables(legPrices[j].getProductKey(),legBuyParticipants[j],legSellParticipants[j],tradePrices[j], ctCommand);
5332                        
5333                        if(tradingProducts[j] != null)
5334                        {
5335                            updateOrderBook(true, null, tradingProducts[j], 
5336                                            legSides[j].isBuySide() ? legBuyParticipants[j] : legSellParticipants[j], 
5337                                            legSides[j].isBuySide() ? legSellParticipants[j] : legBuyParticipants[j]);                 
5338 
5339                        }
5340                    }                   
5341                    
5342                            updateTradables(book.getTradingProduct().getProductKey(), nextBuy, nextSell, tradePrice, ctCommand);
5343                            updateOrderBook(needsBookUpdated, unBookedTradable, book.getTradingProduct(), nextBuy, nextSell);
5344                        
5345                        if (Log.isDebugOn())
5346                        {
5347                            Log.debug("TradeServiceImpl::completeSatisfactionTrades>> creating CreateSpreadTradeCommand for ASYNC_TRADE");
5348                        }
5349                        
5350                                    //CreateSpreadTradeCommand ctCommand =  CreateSpreadTradeCommand.getInstance();
5351                                    ctCommand.setContext(CreateSpreadTradeCommand.DO_TRADE_MATCH_FOR_SPREAD, book.getTradingProduct(),null,
5352                                                    unBookedTradable, nextBuy, legBuyParticipants, nextSell, legSellParticipants,
5353                                                    tradePrice, tradePrices, derivedTradeSide, legPrices);
5354                                    ctCommand.setHeldOrderTrade(true);  
5355                                    ctCommand.setEmitPointContext(epTradeMatch.makeCopyOfThreadContext());
5356                    }
5357                    else
5358                    {
5359                    
5360                            CreateTradeCommand ctCommand =  CreateTradeCommand.getInstance();
5361                            ctCommand.capturePriorTradeData(nextBuy, nextSell);
5362                            
5363                            updateTradables(book.getTradingProduct().getProductKey(), nextBuy, nextSell, tradePrice, ctCommand);
5364                            updateOrderBook(needsBookUpdated, unBookedTradable, book.getTradingProduct(), nextBuy, nextSell);
5365                            
5366                    
5367                                ctCommand.setContext( book.getTradingProduct(),  unBookedTradable,  nextBuy,  nextSell, tradePrice );
5368                                ctCommand.setHeldOrderTrade(true);
5369                    ctCommand.setEmitPointContext(epTradeMatch.makeCopyOfThreadContext());
5370            }
5371            }
5372            else
5373            {
5374            TradeReport report = tradeMatch(book.getTradingProduct(), true/* OSEQ trade */,
5375                    nextBuy, nextSell, tradePrice, null, new HashMap());
5376 
5377                    report.completeTrade(needsBookUpdated, unBookedTradable, true);
5378        }
5379        }
5380    }

5387    /**
5388     */
5389    private int createParticipantListForSatisfaction(ArrayList oppositeSideList,
5390            Enumeration oppositeSideTradables, int tradableQuantity)
5391    {
5392        ParticipantListImpl oppositeParticipantList = new ParticipantListImpl();
5393        int tradedQuantity = 0;
5394        int qty = 0;
5395        int remainingQty = tradableQuantity;
5396        Tradable oppositeTradable;
5397        while (oppositeSideTradables.hasMoreElements() && tradedQuantity < tradableQuantity)
5398        {
5399            oppositeTradable = (Tradable) oppositeSideTradables.nextElement();
5400            qty = (oppositeTradable.getQuantityAllowed() < remainingQty)
5401                    ? oppositeTradable.getQuantityAllowed()
5402                    : remainingQty;
5403 
5404            tradedQuantity += qty;
5405            remainingQty -= qty;
5406 
5407            if (qty != 0)
5408            {
5409                createParticipantItem(oppositeTradable, qty, oppositeParticipantList);
5410            }
5411        }
5412 
5413        oppositeSideList.add(oppositeParticipantList);
5414 
5415        return tradedQuantity;
5416    }
5417 
5418    /**
5419     * Gets next tradable TODO: before this method, oppositeSideMarkets is always called
5420     * sameSideMarkets which one is correct???
5421     */
5422    private Tradable getNextTradable(Tradable currentTradable, Enumeration oppositeSideMarkets,
5423            Tradable lastTradable, int quantityRemaining, TradingClass tradingClass)
5424    {
5425 
5426        if (lastTradable == null && oppositeSideMarkets == null)
5427        {
5428            return null;
5429        }
5430        if (lastTradable != null && currentTradable == lastTradable)
5431        {
5432            return null;
5433        }
5434 
5435        while (oppositeSideMarkets != null && oppositeSideMarkets.hasMoreElements())
5436        {
5437                        Tradable nextTradable = (Tradable) oppositeSideMarkets.nextElement();
5438            if (getMinQuantity(tradingClass, nextTradable) <= quantityRemaining)
5439            {
5440                                return nextTradable;
5441                        }
5442                }
5443        if (lastTradable != null && getMinQuantity(tradingClass, lastTradable) <= quantityRemaining)
5444        {
5445                        return lastTradable;
5446                }
5447                return null;
5448        }
5449 
5450        /**
5451         * Creates a <code>ParticipantItem</code> for the <code>Tradable</code> and adds it to the
5452         * appropriate <code>ParticipantList</code>.  Note that a <code>ParticipantItem</code> will only
5453         * be created if the quantity is greater than 0.
5454         *
5455         * @param tradable                Tradable to have create item for
5456         * @param quantity                quantity being traded
5457         * @param participants        ParticipantList for item
5458         * @since Increment 4
5459         */
5460    private void createParticipantItem(Tradable tradable, int quantity, ParticipantList participants)
5461    {
5462        if (quantity > 0)
5463        {
5464                        ParticipantItem tradableItem = new ParticipantItemImpl(tradable, quantity);
5465                        participants.addElement(tradableItem);
5466                }
5467        }

5469    /**
5470     * Allocate spread tradables based on the price and quantityRequested. Return allocated
5471     * quantity. The allocated quantity may be less than or equal to the quantityRequested. When if
5472     * less, it is because 1. there may be not enough quantity in the book to be allocated. 2. there
5473     * may be contingent tradables whose contingent quantities can not be satisfied by
5474     * quantityRequested
5475     */
5476    protected int allocateSpreadTradables(ParticipantList list, OrderBook anOrderBook,
5477            Price tradePrice, Side sideOfAllocation, int quantityRequested)
5478    {
5479                int remainingQuantity = quantityRequested;
5480                PriorityTradableSet nextSet;
5481        AllocationTradeContextImpl allocationContext;
5482        Iterator prioritySets;
5483        allocationContext = new AllocationTradeContextImpl(AllocationTradeTypes.REGULAR);
5484        prioritySets = anOrderBook.getPrioritySets(sideOfAllocation, tradePrice, quantityRequested,
5485                allocationContext);
5486        while (remainingQuantity > 0 && prioritySets.hasNext())
5487        {
5488                        nextSet = (PriorityTradableSet) prioritySets.next();
5489                        remainingQuantity -= nextSet.allocate(list, remainingQuantity);
5490                        nextSet.resetElements();
5491                }
5492        return quantityRequested - remainingQuantity;
5493        }

5496     * This method obtains the quantity available for trading. This method just returns the actual
5497     * quantity for this implementation. The Stock subclass will redifine this method in order to
5498     * handle Odd and Mixed lots.
5499     * 
5500     */
5501    protected int getAvailableQuantity(TradingClass aTradingClass, Tradable tradable)

5510     */
5511    protected int getAdjustedQuantityForVolumeContingency(OrderBook book, Tradable tradable,

5515        // BookDepthStruct bookDepthStruct = book.getBookDepth(true);

5517        // Enumeration booksOtherSide = book.getTradables(tradable.getSide().getOtherSide());
5518

5520        {

5522            if (bookorder.hasVolumeContingency())
5523            {
5524                    adjustedQuantity += bookorder.getQuantity();
5525                }

5528    }

5564    /**

5566     * on the allocated price and quantity from the other side

5569     * @param inputTradePrices                list of trade prices for each ParticipantList to be created
5570     * @param inputTradeQuantityList        list of trade quantities for each ParticipantList to be created
5571     * @param tradable                            the tradable
5572     * @param sameSideMarkets                            other tradables in the same side
5573     * @param quantityAllocateFromOpposite                total quantity allocate from the opposite side
5574     * @return         total allocated quantity for this side
5575     */
5576    protected int createParticipantLists(ArrayList outputParticipantList,
5577            ArrayList inputTradePrices, ArrayList inputTradeQuantityList, Tradable tradable,
5578            Enumeration sameSideMarkets, int quantityAllocateFromOpposite, TradingClass tradingClass)
5579    {

5581                inputTradeQuantityList, tradable, sameSideMarkets, quantityAllocateFromOpposite,
5582                                    tradingClass, true);
5583    }
5584 
5585    /**
5586     * Creates Lists of ParticipantList from the tradable and its same side market tradables based
5587     * on the allocated price and quantity from the other side
5588     *
5589     * @param outputParticipantList     list of <code> ParticipantList</code> to be created
5590     * @param inputTradePrices                list of trade prices for each ParticipantList to be created
5591     * @param inputTradeQuantityList        list of trade quantities for each ParticipantList to be created
5592     * @param tradable                            the tradable
5593     * @param sameSideMarkets                            other tradables in the same side
5594     * @param quantityAllocateFromOpposite                total quantity allocate from the opposite side
5595     * @param allcoateSameSideBookFirst a flag to indicate to allocate to the markets exisiting in
5596     * the order book first
5597     * @return total allocated quantity for this side
5598     */
5599    public int createParticipantLists(ArrayList outputParticipantList, ArrayList inputTradePrices,
5600            ArrayList inputTradeQuantityList, Tradable tradable, Enumeration sameSideMarkets,
5601            int quantityAllocateFromOpposite, TradingClass tradingClass,
5602            boolean allcoateSameSideBookFirst)
5603    {
5604        Tradable currentTradable = null;
5605        int unallocatedTradableQuantity = 0;
5606        int sameAllocated = 0;
5607        int remainingQuantity = quantityAllocateFromOpposite;
5608        for (int i = 0; i < inputTradeQuantityList.size() && remainingQuantity > 0; i++)
5609        {
5610            // Price oppositePrice = (Price) inputTradePrices.get(i);
5611            int currentQuantity = ((Integer) inputTradeQuantityList.get(i)).intValue();
5612            ParticipantList currentSame = new ParticipantListImpl();
5613            while (currentQuantity > 0)
5614            {
5615                if (unallocatedTradableQuantity == 0)
5616                {
5617                    if (allcoateSameSideBookFirst)
5618                    {
5619                        currentTradable = getNextTradable(currentTradable, sameSideMarkets,
5620                                tradable, remainingQuantity, tradingClass);
5621                    }
5622                    else
5623                    {
5624                        currentTradable = getNextTradableFromCurrent(currentTradable,
5625                                sameSideMarkets, tradable, remainingQuantity, tradingClass);
5626                    }
5627                    if (currentTradable == null)
5628                    {
5629                        // We ran out of quantity on the new tradable side so we want to break out
5630                        // of the loop.
5631                        remainingQuantity = 0;
5632                        break;
5633                    }
5634                    unallocatedTradableQuantity = getAvailableQuantity(tradingClass,
5635                            currentTradable);
5636                }
5637                int currentAllocation;
5638                if (unallocatedTradableQuantity > currentQuantity)
5639                {
5640                    currentAllocation = currentQuantity;
5641                }
5642                else
5643                {
5644                    currentAllocation = unallocatedTradableQuantity;
5645                }
5646                createParticipantItem(currentTradable, currentAllocation, currentSame);
5647                unallocatedTradableQuantity -= currentAllocation;
5648                currentQuantity -= currentAllocation;
5649                remainingQuantity -= currentAllocation;
5650                sameAllocated += currentAllocation;
5651            }
5652 
5653            outputParticipantList.add(currentSame);
5654        }
5655        return sameAllocated;

5658    protected String getPreferredFirmExchange(Tradable tradable)

5679    protected List getPreferredFirmAcronym(Tradable tradable)
5680    {
5681        List preferredFirmAcronym = null;
5682        // check if this is a PreferredDPM's Preferred Firm, and try to get a FirmID
5683        if (tradable != null && tradable instanceof Order)
5684        {
5685            Order thisOrder = null;
5686            try
5687            {
5688                do
5689                {
5690                        thisOrder = (Order) tradable;
5691 
5692                    String extensions = thisOrder.getExtensions();
5693 
5694                    if (ValueObject.isEmpty(extensions))
5695                        break;
5696 
5697                    preferredFirmAcronym = deCodeExtensionsCompatible(extensions);
5698 
5699                    if (preferredFirmAcronym == null || preferredFirmAcronym.size() == 0)
5700                            break;
5701                    Log.information(this, "preferredFirmAcronym(" + preferredFirmAcronym
5702                            + ") Order(" + thisOrder + ")");
5703                } while (false);
5704            }
5705            catch (Exception ex)
5706            {
5707                Log.alarm(this, "Unable to get PDPM from extensions field for Order(" + thisOrder
5708                        + ") exception: " + ex);
5709            }
5710        }
5711 
5712        return preferredFirmAcronym;
5713    }

5715    /**

5731    private int createParticipantLists(ArrayList outputParticipantList,

5734            OrderBook book, Side tradableSide, Price endingPrice, int quantityToAllocate,
5735            boolean nonQTrade, boolean needsSingleFillOnly, boolean treatedLikeCustomerTrade,
5736            Tradable tradable, boolean nonContingency)
5737    {
5738        int allocatedQuantity = 0;
5739        ParticipantList currentOpposite = null;
5740        Price currentPrice = new NoPrice();
5741        int allocatedAtCurrentPrice = 0;
5742        AllocationTradeContextImpl allocationContext;
5743        Iterator sets;
5744 
5745        int legRatio = 1;
5746 
5747        if(tradable!=null && !aProduct.isStrategy())
5748        {
5749                legRatio = calculateLegRatio(tradable.getProductKey(), aProduct.getProductKey());
5750        }
5751 
5752        // setting up the required details in allocation context

5754        allocationContext.setNonQAllocation(nonQTrade);
5755        allocationContext.setTreatedLikeCustomerAllocation(treatedLikeCustomerTrade);
5756        allocationContext.setNonContingencyAllocation(nonContingency);
5757

5759        if(tradable != null && !(preferredFirmAcronym != null && preferredFirmAcronym.size() > 0))
5760        {
5761                preferredFirmAcronym = getPreferredFirmAcronym(tradable);
5762                allocationContext.setQtyForPmmAllocation(tradable.getQuantityAllowed()*legRatio);
5763        }
5764

5766        
5767        if (preferredFirmAcronym != null && preferredFirmAcronym.size() != 0)
5768        {
5769            allocationContext.setPreferredFirm(preferredFirmAcronym);
5770                            if (preferredFirmExchange == null || preferredFirmExchange.length() == 0)
5771                            {
5772                                preferredFirmExchange = "CBOE";
5773                            }
5774 
5775                }
5776 
5777        sets = book.getPrioritySets(tradableSide, endingPrice, quantityToAllocate,
5778                allocationContext);
5779        while (sets.hasNext() && allocatedQuantity < quantityToAllocate)
5780        {
5781            PriorityTradableSet nextSet = (PriorityTradableSet) sets.next();
5782            if (nextSet.getPrice() != currentPrice && !currentPrice.isNoPrice()
5783                    && needsSingleFillOnly)
5784            {
5785                break;
5786            }
5787            else if (nextSet.getPrice() != currentPrice)
5788            {
5789                // The first time through, currentPrice will be a NoPrice.
5790                // If this is not the first time through, we have hit a new price that we
5791                // need to allocate quantity for, so we save the last price information.
5792                if (!currentPrice.isNoPrice())
5793                {
5794                    outputTradePrices.add(TradeHelper.determineTradePrice(tradableSide,
5795                            currentPrice, aProduct));
5796                    outputTradeQuantityList.add(new Integer(allocatedAtCurrentPrice));
5797                    outputParticipantList.add(currentOpposite);
5798                }
5799                // get ready to allocate quantity at a new price.
5800                currentOpposite = new ParticipantListImpl();
5801                currentPrice = nextSet.getPrice();
5802                allocatedAtCurrentPrice = 0;
5803            }
5804            int nextAllocatedQuantity = nextSet.allocate(currentOpposite, quantityToAllocate
5805                    - allocatedQuantity);
5806            allocatedQuantity += nextAllocatedQuantity;
5807            allocatedAtCurrentPrice += nextAllocatedQuantity;
5808        }
5809        if (allocatedQuantity > 0)
5810        {
5811            // If we were able to find opposite side quantity, we now need to create corresponding
5812            // participant lists for the same side tradables (the new one and any we are trading
5813            // ahead)

5815                    aProduct));
5816            outputTradeQuantityList.add(new Integer(allocatedAtCurrentPrice));
5817            outputParticipantList.add(currentOpposite);
5818        }

6032    /**
6033     * Creates a <code>ParticipantList</code> for a trade at the given price and quantity on the
6034     * given side. The <code>ParticipantItem</code>s in the list will need to be matched with
6035     * <code>ParticipantItem</code>s on the opposite side in order for the trade to be complete.
6036     * 
6037     */
6038 
6039    private ParticipantList createParticipantListForOpening(OrderBook currentOrderBook,
6040            Side tradableSide, Price tradePrice, int tradeQuantity)
6041    {
6042        ParticipantList participants = new ParticipantListImpl();
6043        int allocatedQuantity = 0;
6044        AllocationTradeContext allocationContext = new AllocationTradeContextImpl(
6045                AllocationTradeTypes.OPENING);
6046        Iterator sets = currentOrderBook.getPrioritySets(tradableSide, tradePrice, tradeQuantity,
6047                allocationContext);
6048        PriorityTradableSet nextSet = null;
6049        int nextAllocatedQuantity = 0;
6050        ParticipantList currentList = null;
6051 
6052        while (sets.hasNext() && allocatedQuantity < tradeQuantity)
6053        {
6054            nextSet = (PriorityTradableSet) sets.next();
6055 
6056            currentList = new ParticipantListImpl();
6057            nextAllocatedQuantity = nextSet
6058                    .allocate(currentList, tradeQuantity - allocatedQuantity);
6059            allocatedQuantity += nextAllocatedQuantity;
6060 
6061            // add to the same list since it will be traded all at the same openingPrice
6062            addParticipantToList(currentList, participants);
6063        }
6064 
6065        return participants;
6066    }

6068    protected void addParticipantToList(ParticipantList fromList, ParticipantList toList)
6069    {
6070        if (toList == null || fromList == null)
6071        {
6072            throw new IllegalArgumentException("The List trying to add is NULL");
6073        }
6074        Enumeration participantItemsEnum = fromList.elements();
6075 
6076        while (participantItemsEnum.hasMoreElements())
6077        {
6078            toList.addElement((ParticipantItem) participantItemsEnum.nextElement());
6079        }
6080 
6081    }
6082 
6083    /**
6084     * Creates a <code>ParticipantList</code> for a trade at the given price and quantity on the
6085     * given side. The <code>ParticipantItem</code>s in the list will need to be matched with
6086     * <code>ParticipantItem</code>s on the opposite side in order for the trade to be complete.
6087     * 
6088     */
6089    private ParticipantList createParticipantList(Tradable incomingMarketOrder,
6090            OrderBook currentOrderBook, Side tradableSide, Price tradePrice, int tradeQuantity,
6091            boolean allowContingencies, final boolean marketOrderTrade)
6092    {
6093        // If we receive an incoming market order we must verify it is a market
6094        // order AND the caller is invoking this method for a market order trade
6095        if (incomingMarketOrder != null)
6096        {
6097            if (!incomingMarketOrder.getPrice().isMarketPrice())
6098            {
6099                throw new IllegalArgumentException("method createParticipantList "
6100                        + "received incoming market tradable argument that is not "
6101                        + " a market order!");
6102            }
6103            if (!marketOrderTrade)
6104            {
6105                throw new IllegalArgumentException("method createParticipantList "
6106                        + "called with an incoming market order but marketOrderTrade "
6107                        + "flag is not set as true!");
6108            }
6109        }
6110        ParticipantList participants = new ParticipantListImpl();
6111        int remainingQuantity = tradeQuantity;
6112 
6113        Enumeration tradables;
6114        if (marketOrderTrade)
6115        {
6116            // We only want market orders.
6117            tradables = currentOrderBook.getTradables(tradableSide, PriceFactory
6118                    .create(Price.MARKET_STRING), true);
6119        }
6120        else
6121        {
6122            tradables = currentOrderBook.getTradables(tradableSide);
6123        }
6124 
6125        Tradable nextTradable;
6126        if (tradables.hasMoreElements())
6127        {
6128            nextTradable = (Tradable) tradables.nextElement();
6129        }
6130        else
6131        {
6132            nextTradable = incomingMarketOrder;
6133            incomingMarketOrder = null;
6134        }
6135 
6136        TradingClass tradingClass = currentOrderBook.getTradingProduct().getTradingClass();
6137 
6138        while (remainingQuantity > 0 && nextTradable != null)
6139        {
6140 
6141            // if this is a market order trade, verify the tradable is a market order!
6142            if (marketOrderTrade && !nextTradable.getPrice().isMarketPrice())
6143            {
6144                // If this happens, we've got a code problem.
6145                // The getTradables call on the order book above in this method is supposed
6146                // to be returning only market orders.  Here that didn't happen.
6147                throw new IllegalArgumentException(
6148                        "Invalid order for market order trade: Price is not MKT.");
6149            }
6150 
6151            // end search if current price is not better or equal to trade price
6152            if (!tradableSide.isFirstBetterOrEqual(nextTradable.getPrice(), tradePrice))
6153            {
6154                break;
6155            }
6156            // skip volume contingencies if they are either not allowed or cannot be satisfied by
6157            // the remaining
6158            // quantity.
6159            if (!nextTradable.hasVolumeContingency()
6160                    || (allowContingencies && getMinQuantity(tradingClass, nextTradable) <= remainingQuantity))
6161            {
6162                int tradableQuantity = getAvailableQuantity(tradingClass, nextTradable);
6163                if (tradableQuantity > remainingQuantity)
6164                {
6165                    tradableQuantity = remainingQuantity;
6166                }
6167                createParticipantItem(nextTradable, tradableQuantity, participants);
6168                remainingQuantity -= tradableQuantity;
6169            }
6170 
6171            if (tradables.hasMoreElements())
6172            {
6173                nextTradable = (Tradable) tradables.nextElement();
6174            }
6175            else
6176            {
6177                nextTradable = incomingMarketOrder;
6178                incomingMarketOrder = null;
6179            }
6180        }
6181        return participants;
6182    }
