6184        /**
6185         * Creates trade report for spread product for matched tradables.
6186         *
6187         */
6188    public TradeReport doTradeMatchForSpread(TradingProduct tradingProduct, char tradeType,
6189            char settlementTradeType, boolean heldOrderTrade, ParticipantList biders,
6190            ParticipantList askers, Price tradePrice, Tradable tradable,
6191            boolean isQualifiedContingentTrade, Side derivedTradeSide, StrategyLegTradePrice[] legPrices,

6195    throws SpreadProcessingException, DataValidationException, SystemException

6198        // call

6201TradingClass tClass = tradingProduct.getTradingClass();
6202            if(!isAsynchronousTradingEnabled(tradingProduct))
6203            {

6207            }

6221                heldOrderTrade, biders, askers, tradePrice, null /* no parent report */,isAsynchronousTrade, participantFills ,tradeReportParam);

6225            generateTradeReportForLegs(biders, context, askers, tradeReport,

6229            //coz this is really calling TSCPI.generateTradeReportForLegs which do tradeReport.completeTrade already.

6260                }
6261                if (Log.isDebugOn())

6273       
6274    private StrategyLegTradePrice[] getLegPrices(TradingProduct tradingProduct, 
6275                                                ParticipantList biders, ParticipantList askers, Price tradePrice, 
6276                                                boolean isQualifiedContingentTrade, boolean isTBForCOB)
6277    throws SpreadProcessingException, DataValidationException, SystemException
6278    {
6279            StrategyLegTradePrice[] legPrices = null;
6280        if (biders.isRegularList() && askers.isRegularList())
6281        { // spread order trade with spread order
6282            //derivedTradeSide = null;    /* value will not be used */
6283            
6284            //For QCT Trades, use a different leg trade price calculations.
6285            if(isQualifiedContingentTrade)
6286            {
6287                legPrices = calculateQCTTradePricesForLegs(biders, askers, tradePrice, tradingProduct);
6288                validateQCTLegTradePrices(tradingProduct, legPrices);
6289                //Check if the leg trade prices are at or within NBBO
6290            }
6291            else if(tradingProduct.getTradingClass().isFlexStrategyProduct(tradingProduct))
6292            {
6293                legPrices = calculateTradePricesForFlexStrategyLegs(biders, askers, tradePrice, tradingProduct);
6294            }
6295            else//Non QCT Trade.
6296            {
6297                    legPrices = calculateTradePricesForLegs(biders, askers, tradePrice, tradingProduct, isTBForCOB);
6298            }
6299        }
6300        else if (biders.isDerivedList() && askers.isRegularList())
6301        {
6302            legPrices = biders.getLegTradePrices();
6303        }
6304        else if (biders.isRegularList() && askers.isDerivedList())
6305        {
6306            legPrices = askers.getLegTradePrices();
6307        }
6308        else
6309        {
6310            throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(
6311                    "Unexpected combination of participant list types for trade", 0);
6312        }
6313        return legPrices;
6314    }
6315        
6316        
6317        /**
6318         * Do the following validations for leg Trade prices:
6319         * 1. Must be at or within NBBO.
6320         * 2. Must be better than customer on legs.
6321         * 3. Must be in standard incremental prices.
6322         * 
6323         * @param tradingProduct
6324         * @param legPrices
6325         * @throws DataValidationException
6326         * @throws SpreadProcessingException
6327         * @throws SystemException
6328         */
6329        protected void validateQCTLegTradePrices(TradingProduct tradingProduct, StrategyLegTradePrice[] legPrices) throws DataValidationException, SpreadProcessingException, SystemException
6330        {
6331                boolean isSTSEnabled = ((TradingProductImpl)tradingProduct).isRolledoutSpreadClass();
6332                NBBOStruct[] nbbo = null;
6333                // If sts is disabled, get the NBBO from tradingProduct, else do a quoteQuery to 
6334        if(!isSTSEnabled)
6335        {
6336                nbbo = new NBBOStruct[legPrices.length];
6337                for(int i = 0;i<legPrices.length;i++)
6338                {
6339                        nbbo[i] = legPrices[i].getTradingProduct().getNBBO(
6340                            tradingProduct.getTradingClass().getSessionName());
6341                }
6342        }
6343        else
6344                {
6345                        int[] legProductKeys = new int[legPrices.length];
6346                        for(int i =0;i<legPrices.length;i++)
6347                        {
6348                                legProductKeys[i] = legPrices[i].getProductKey();//Gathering the legProduct keys to enable one time quotequery.
6349                        }
6350                        MarketDataService mds = StrategyTradeServiceHelper.getMarketDataServiceRoutingHome().find();
6351                        QuoteQueryV3Struct[] quoteQueryV3Struct = null;
6352                        String sessionName = legPrices[0].getTradingProduct().getTradingClass().getSessionName();
6353                        try
6354                        {
6355                                quoteQueryV3Struct = mds.getQuoteQueryDataForProductsV3(sessionName, legProductKeys);
6356                        }
6357                        catch(Exception e)
6358                        {
6359                                Log.exception("Failed to get NBBO markets for session=" + sessionName
6360                                                      + "; product key=" + legPrices[0].getProductKey(), e);
6361                                      throw ExceptionBuilder.systemException("Failed to get NBBO markets for session=" + sessionName
6362                                                      + "; product key=" + legPrices[0].getProductKey(), 0);
6363                        }
6364                          nbbo = new NBBOStruct[quoteQueryV3Struct.length];
6365                                      for (int i = 0; i < quoteQueryV3Struct.length; i++)
6366                              {
6367                                              nbbo[i] = quoteQueryV3Struct[i].quoteQueryV2Struct.nbboStruct;
6368                              }
6369        }
6370        
6371                                      for(int i =0;i<legPrices.length;i++)
6372                        {
6373                                for(Price legTradePrice : legPrices[i].getTradePrices())
6374                                {
6375                         // 1. validate leg trade prices against nbbo
6376                                        if(!isAtOrWithinNBBO(legTradePrice, nbbo[i]))
6377                                        {
6378                                    throw new SpreadProcessingException(
6379                            "TradServiceImpl.doTradeMatchForSpreadQCT : QCT Leg Trade price "
6380                                                    + legTradePrice + " is outside NBBO ( "
6381                                                    + PriceFactory.create(nbbo[i].bidPrice) + " , "
6382                                    + PriceFactory.create(nbbo[i].askPrice) + " )  " +legPrices[i].getProductKey()+">>>",
6383                                                         SpreadProcessingException.AtLeastOneCalculatedLegPriceTouchesBook);
6384                                        }
6385                            //2. validate leg trade prices against resting customer
6386                            if(!isQCTLegTradePricesBetterThanCustomer(legTradePrice,legPrices[i].getProductKey()))
6387                        {
6388                                throw new SpreadProcessingException(
6389                            "TradServiceImpl.doTradeMatchForSpreadQCT : QCT Leg Trade price "
6390                                    + legPrices[i].getTradePrice() + " is worse than or equal to resting customer order price for the leg "+legPrices[i].getProductKey()+">>>",
6391                                     SpreadProcessingException.AtLeastOneCalculatedLegPriceTouchesBook);
6392                        }
6393                //3. Check if leg trade prices are standard increment prices for that leg.
6394                if(!isLegTradePriceStandardIncrementPriceForTheLeg(legTradePrice,legPrices[i].getTradingProduct().getTradingClass().getProductClassKey()))
6395                {
6396                        throw new SpreadProcessingException(
6397                            "TradServiceImpl.doTradeMatchForSpreadQCT : QCT Leg Trade price "
6398                                    + legPrices[i].getTradePrice() + " is not a standard incremental price for this leg"+ ") "+legPrices[i].getProductKey()+" >>>",
6399                            SpreadProcessingException.LegPricesCanNotBeCalculated);
6400                }
6401                    }
6402            }
6403        }
6404        
6405        /**
6406         * Compare leg price with customer price on legs. 
6407         * 
6408         * @param leg
6409         * @return
6410         * @throws DataValidationException
6411         */
6412        protected boolean isQCTLegTradePricesBetterThanCustomer(Price legTradePrice, int productKey) throws DataValidationException
6413        {
6414                OrderBook book  = null;
6415                boolean result = true;
6416                Price bidSideCustomerPrice = PriceFactory.create(Price.NO_PRICE_STRING);;
6417                Price askSideCustomerPrice = PriceFactory.create(Price.NO_PRICE_STRING);;
6418                try
6419                {
6420                        book = getOrderBook(productKey);
6421                }
6422                catch( DataValidationException e)
6423                {
6424                 Log.information("TradeServiceImpl.legPricesBetterThanRestingCustomerOrderOnLegs>>>>>" +
6425                                 " OrderBook not found for product"+productKey);  
6426                 throw new DataValidationException("TradeServiceImpl.legPricesBetterThanRestingCustomerOrderOnLegs>>>>>" +
6427                                         " OrderBook not found for product",e.details);
6428                }
6429                
6430                if(book.getBestCustomerOrderQuantity(SideFactory.getBuySide()) > 0)
6431                {
6432                        bidSideCustomerPrice  = book.getBestPrice(SideFactory.getBuySide());
6433                }
6434                if(book.getBestCustomerOrderQuantity(SideFactory.getSellSide()) > 0)
6435                {
6436                        askSideCustomerPrice  = book.getBestPrice(SideFactory.getSellSide());
6437                }
6438                
6439                if((!bidSideCustomerPrice.isNoPrice() && legTradePrice.lessThanOrEqual(bidSideCustomerPrice)) ||
6440                                (!askSideCustomerPrice.isNoPrice()&& legTradePrice.greaterThanOrEqual(askSideCustomerPrice)))
6441                {
6442                        result = false;
6443                }
6444            return result;
6445        }
6446 
6447    /**
6448     * Check if the leg trade prices are at standard increment prices for that class.
6449     * @param product
6450     * @param legTradePrice
6451     * @return
6452     * @throws SystemException
6453     * @throws DataValidationException
6454     */
6455    protected boolean isLegTradePriceStandardIncrementPriceForTheLeg(Price legTradePrice, int classKey )throws SystemException, DataValidationException
6456    {
6457            ProductClassData prodClass = null;
6458            try 
6459            {
6460            prodClass = getProductDataCacheHome().find().getProductClassData(classKey);
6461        } 
6462            catch (NotFoundException e)
6463            {
6464            throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(("Invalid class key: " + classKey + "."),
6465                    DataValidationCodes.INVALID_PRODUCT);
6466        }
6467        if(!prodClass.isValidPriceForOrder(legTradePrice))
6468        {
6469                return false;
6470        }
6471        return true;
6472    }

6475    public Side getDerivedTradeSide(ParticipantList biders, ParticipantList askers)
6476    throws DataValidationException
6477    {
6478        Side derivedTradeSide = null;
6479        if (biders.isRegularList() && askers.isRegularList())
6480        {
6481            //value returned as null as it is not used
6482        }
6483        else if (biders.isDerivedList() && askers.isRegularList())
6484        {
6485            derivedTradeSide = SideFactory.getAsDefinedSide();            
6486        }
6487        else if (biders.isRegularList() && askers.isDerivedList())
6488        {
6489            derivedTradeSide = SideFactory.getOppositeSide();            
6490        }
6491        else
6492        {

6495        }

6497    }    
6498    
6499    
6500        /**
6501         * Checks if the leg trade price is within NBBO
6502         * 
6503         * @param legTradePrice
6504         * @param nbbo
6505         * @author Cognizant Technology Solutions.
6506         */
6507        protected boolean isAtOrWithinNBBO(Price legTradePrice, NBBOStruct nbbo)
6508    {
6509            if (null != nbbo)
6510        {
6511            Price bidPrice = PriceFactory.create(nbbo.bidPrice);
6512            Price askPrice = PriceFactory.create(nbbo.askPrice);
6513            if (bidPrice.isValuedPrice() && askPrice.isValuedPrice())
6514            {
6515                return legTradePrice.greaterThanOrEqual(bidPrice)
6516                        && legTradePrice.lessThanOrEqual(askPrice);
6517            }
6518            else
6519            {
6520                return true;
6521            }
6522        }
6523        else
6524        {
6525            return true;
6526        }
6527    }

6538        /**

6550            {

6552                        }
6553            else
6554            {
6555                                tempList.add(legPrices[i].getTradePrice());
6556                        }
6557                }
6558                Price[] prices = new Price[tempList.size()];

6599                {
6600                    tempList.add(legTradePrice.getProductKey());
6601                }
6602            }

6606            }

6612        /**

6614         *

6617     * prices will be associated with that leg. The TradingProduct of that leg will be in the

6624        {
6625            if (legPrices[i].splitTradingEmployed())
6626            {
6627                for (int j = 0; j < legPrices[i].getSplitRatios().length; j++)
6628                {
6629                    tempList.add(legPrices[i].getTradingProduct());
6630                }
6631            }
6632            else
6633            {
6634                                tempList.add(legPrices[i].getTradingProduct());
6635                        }
6636                }
6637                TradingProduct[] products = new TradingProduct[tempList.size()];
6638                tempList.toArray(products);
6639                return products;
6640        }

6874    /**
6875     * getTradeReportCollection
6876     * 
6877     * @param broker
6878     * @param firm
6879     * @param sessionName
6880     * @param beginTime <code>DateTimeStruct</code>
6881     * @param endTime   <code>DateTimeStruct</code>
6882     * @param buySellInd -flag to indicates buy or sell side
6883     * @param activeOnly -flag to indicates active reports only or not
6884     * @return TradeReportStructV2[]
6885     * @exception NotFoundException AuthorizationException, SystemException, CommunicationException
6886     *
6887     * Mei Wu
6888     */
6889    private TradeReport[] getTradeReportCollection(ExchangeAcronymStruct broker,
6890            ExchangeFirmStruct firm, int productKey, String sessionName, DateTimeStruct beginTime,
6891            DateTimeStruct endTime, char buySellInd, boolean activeOnly)
6892            throws AuthorizationException, NotFoundException, DataValidationException,
6893            SystemException, CommunicationException
6894    {
6895        TradingSessionStruct tradingSessionStruct = TradingSessionNameHelper
6896                .getSession(sessionName);
6897        if (tradingSessionStruct == null)
6898        {
6899            Log.alarm(this,
6900                    "getTradeReportCollection => getTradeReports query for invalid session name: "
6901                            + sessionName);
6902            throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException("Invalid session name: " + sessionName,
6903                    DataValidationCodes.INVALID_SESSION);
6904        }
6905        if ((beginTime.date.year == 0 && endTime.date.year != 0)
6906                || (beginTime.date.year != 0 && endTime.date.year == 0))
6907        {
6908            String msg  =  "Invalid begin/end dates: both begin and end time must be present or 0s";
6909            Log.alarm(this, "getTradeReportCollection => " + msg);
6910            throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(msg, DataValidationCodes.INVALID_TIME);
6911        }
6912        else if (beginTime.date.year == 0 && endTime.date.year == 0)
6913        {
6914            // get the trade report from the start time of the current session to end time of the
6915            // session
6916            DateWrapper dateWrapper = new DateWrapper();
6917            dateWrapper.setTime(tradingSessionStruct.startTime);
6918            beginTime = dateWrapper.toDateTimeStruct();
6919            dateWrapper.setTime(tradingSessionStruct.endTime);
6920            endTime = dateWrapper.toDateTimeStruct();
6921        }
6922 
6923        // ensure that this trade service is configured to accept trades for this
6924        // session by getting the strategy for the session name
6925        // DataValidationException is thrown if an error occurs.
6926 
6927        // use default product type 0, to get a generic tradeValidationStrategy to validate the
6928        // trade report query
6929        // for real trade, we need to pass a meaning productType to get an appropriate trade
6930        // validation strategy
6931        getTradeValidationStrategy(sessionName, 0);
6932        validateFirm(firm);
6933        if (!broker.acronym.equals("") || !broker.exchange.equals(""))
6934        {
6935            validateUser(broker); // broker is optional in this call.
6936        }
6937        validateProduct(productKey);
6938        TradeReport[] reports = null;
6939        try
6940        {
6941            reports = getTradeReportHome().findTradeReports(broker, firm, productKey, sessionName,
6942                    beginTime, endTime, buySellInd, activeOnly);
6943        }
6944        finally
6945        {
6946            if (reports == null)
6947            {
6948                reports = new TradeReport[0];
6949            }
6950        }
6951        return reports;
6952    }

6965            throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException("Invalid firm number: "

7064    /**
7065     * creat a pending trade for the quote trigger
7066     */
7067    public int createPendingTrade(OrderBook book, QuoteTriggerTradable aQuoteTrigger)
7068            throws SpreadProcessingException, DataValidationException, SystemException
7069    {
7070        int allocatedQuantity = 0;
7071        boolean success = false;
7072        boolean isStrategy = book.getTradingProduct().isStrategy();
7073 
7074        try
7075        {
7076            Transaction.startTransaction();
7077 
7078            Side otherSide = aQuoteTrigger.getSide().getOtherSide();
7079            int quantityToAllocate = aQuoteTrigger.getQuantityAllowed();
7080            Price triggerPrice = aQuoteTrigger.getNonQPrice();
7081            Price localTradePrice = triggerPrice;
7082            TradingProduct aProduct = book.getTradingProduct();
7083            ArrayList nonQParticipantLists = new ArrayList();
7084            ArrayList tradePrices = new ArrayList();
7085            ArrayList tradeQuantities = new ArrayList();
7086            int nonQAllocatedQuantity = createParticipantLists(nonQParticipantLists, tradePrices,
7087                    tradeQuantities, getPreferredFirmAcronym(aQuoteTrigger),
7088                    getPreferredFirmExchange(aQuoteTrigger), aProduct, book, otherSide,
7089                    triggerPrice, quantityToAllocate, true, false, false, null, false);
7090            if (nonQAllocatedQuantity > 0)
7091            {
7092                ArrayList triggerParticipantLists = new ArrayList();
7093                int triggerSideAllocatedQuantity = createParticipantLists(triggerParticipantLists,
7094                        tradePrices, tradeQuantities, aQuoteTrigger, null, nonQAllocatedQuantity,
7095                        aProduct.getTradingClass());
7096                if (triggerSideAllocatedQuantity != nonQAllocatedQuantity)
7097                {
7098                    allocatedQuantity = 0;
7099                }
7100                else
7101                {
7102                    allocatedQuantity = triggerSideAllocatedQuantity;
7103                    Tradable unBookedTradable = aQuoteTrigger;
7104                    QuoteTriggerTradeReport aTradeReport = aQuoteTrigger.getPendingTradeReport();
7105                    if (aTradeReport == null)
7106                    {
7107                        if (aQuoteTrigger.isAsDefinedSide())
7108                        {
7109                            double value = -1 * localTradePrice.toDouble();
7110                            localTradePrice = PriceFactory.create(value);
7111                        }
7112 
7113                        aTradeReport = getTradeReportHome().createQuoteTriggerTradeReport(aProduct,
7114                                localTradePrice, aQuoteTrigger.getSide(), myIdService);
7115                        aQuoteTrigger.setPendingTradeReport(aTradeReport);
7116                    }
7117                    // 12/11/04, need to publish ticker/last sale for spread legs at time of quote
7118                    // trigger creation
7119                    if (isStrategy)
7120                    {
7121                        saveLegPricesAtQTCreation(book, aTradeReport, aQuoteTrigger);
7122                    }
7123                    aTradeReport.addTrade(triggerParticipantLists, nonQParticipantLists,
7124                            tradePrices, tradeQuantities, unBookedTradable);
7125                }
7126            }
7127 
7128            if (allocatedQuantity > 0)
7129            {
7130                success = Transaction.commit();
7131            }
7132            else
7133            {
7134                Transaction.rollback();
7135                success = true;
7136            }
7137        }
7138        finally
7139        {
7140            if (!success)
7141            {
7142                Log.alarm(this, "createPendingTrade failed for " + aQuoteTrigger.toString() + ".");
7143                Transaction.rollback();
7144            }
7145        }
7146        return  allocatedQuantity;
7147    }
7148 
7149    /*
7150     * UD 12/15/04 calculate the leg prices at time of QT creation and save them in
7151     * QuoteTriggerTradable.
7152    */
7153    private void saveLegPricesAtQTCreation(OrderBook book, QuoteTriggerTradeReport aTradeReport,
7154            QuoteTriggerTradable aQuoteTrigger) throws DataValidationException,
7155            SpreadProcessingException, SystemException
7156    {
7157        StrategyLegTradePrice[] strategyLegTradePrices;
7158        aTradeReport.prepareForCompletion();
7159        Side derivedTradeSide = null;
7160        Price localTradePrice = aQuoteTrigger.getNonQPrice();
7161        if (aQuoteTrigger.isAsDefinedSide())
7162        {
7163            double value = -1 * localTradePrice.toDouble();
7164            localTradePrice = PriceFactory.create(value);
7165        }
7166        strategyLegTradePrices = getLegPrices(book.getTradingProduct(), localTradePrice,
7167                aTradeReport.getBidList(), aTradeReport.getAskList(), derivedTradeSide);
7168        Price[] tradePricesOfLegs = getTradePricesFrom(strategyLegTradePrices);
7169        // Following introduced when noticed that if a split occurs num(Prices) >
7170        // num(strategyLegTradePrices)
7171        // Currently, its commented out based on decision that tickValue(strategy) will not be less
7172        // than tickValue(legs)
7173//       TradingProduct[] tradingProducts = getTradingProductsFrom(strategyLegTradePrices);
7174//       aTradeReport.setTradingProductsFromLegTradePrices(tradingProducts);
7175        Side[] legSides = getLegSidesFrom(strategyLegTradePrices);
7176        aTradeReport.setStrategyLegTradePrices(strategyLegTradePrices);
7177        aTradeReport.setTradePricesOfLegs(tradePricesOfLegs);
7178        aTradeReport.setSidesOfLegs(legSides);
7179        aTradeReport.setDerivedTradeSide(derivedTradeSide);
7180    }

7182    /**
7183     * complete the pending trade for QuoteTrigger
7184     */
7185    public void completePendingTrade(OrderBook book, QuoteTriggerTradable aQuoteTrigger)
7186            throws DataValidationException, SystemException
7187    {
7188        try
7189        {
7190            internalCompletePendingTrade(book, aQuoteTrigger);
7191        }
7192        catch (RuntimeException ex)
7193        {
7194            // Since the interceptor is occasionally failing to log the stack trace, do it here.
7195            //
7196            Log.exception(this, "Runtime exception in completePendingTrade: " + ex, ex);
7197            Log.alarm("Runtime exception " + ex + " in completePendingTrade(book.product="
7198                    + book.getProductKey() + ", trigger.side=" + aQuoteTrigger.getSide()
7199                    + ", trigger.price=" + aQuoteTrigger.getPrice() + ")");
7200            throw ex; // (re-throw)
7201        }
7202    }
7203 
7204    /**
7205     *  Refactored from completePendingTrade to add runtime exception logging.
7206     */
7207    private void internalCompletePendingTrade(OrderBook book, QuoteTriggerTradable aQuoteTrigger)
7208            throws DataValidationException, SystemException
7209    {
7210        QuoteTriggerTradeReport aTradeReport = aQuoteTrigger.getPendingTradeReport();
7211        if (aTradeReport == null)
7212        {
7213            Log.alarm("TradeServiceImpl >>> The QuoteTrigger has not TradeReport yet");
7214            return;
7215        }
7216        aTradeReport.prepareForCompletion();
7217        int quantity = aTradeReport.getQuantity();
7218        ParticipantList finalList = new ParticipantListImpl();
7219        int allocatedQuantity = createParticipantListForQuoteTrigger(finalList, book,
7220                aQuoteTrigger, quantity);
7221        if (quantity != allocatedQuantity)
7222        {
7223            Log.alarm("TradeServiceImpl >>> allocated quantity does not match traded quantity "
7224                    + quantity + ":" + allocatedQuantity);
7225            throw ExceptionBuilder.systemException(
7226                    "matched quantity does not match traded quantity " + quantity + ":"
7227                            + allocatedQuantity, 0);
7228        }
7229        aTradeReport.setQuoteTriggerParticipantList(finalList);
7230 
7231        // get final buyers and sellers
7232        ParticipantList buyers = aTradeReport.getBidList();
7233        ParticipantList sellers = aTradeReport.getAskList();
7234        ArrayList atomicTrades = new ArrayList();
7235        int matchQuantity = createAtomicTrades(buyers, sellers, atomicTrades, book
7236                .getTradingProduct());
7237        if (allocatedQuantity != matchQuantity)
7238        {
7239            Log.alarm("TradeServiceImpl >>> matched quantity does not match traded quantity "
7240                    + allocatedQuantity + ":" + matchQuantity);
7241            throw ExceptionBuilder.systemException(
7242                    "matched quantity does not match traded quantity " + allocatedQuantity + ":"
7243                            + matchQuantity, 0);
7244        }
7245 
7246        // UD 10/07/04...
7247        // create atomic trades for the strategy legs.
7248        HashMap buySideLegsMap = new HashMap();
7249        HashMap sellSideLegsMap = new HashMap();
7250        if (book.getTradingProduct().getProductKeys().productType == ProductTypes.STRATEGY)
7251        {
7252            try
7253            {
7254                createStrategyLegsAtomicTrades(book, aQuoteTrigger, buyers, sellers, aTradeReport,
7255                        buySideLegsMap, sellSideLegsMap);
7256            }
7257            catch (SpreadProcessingException spe)
7258            {
7259                Log
7260                        .exception(
7261                                this,
7262                                "createSpreadLegsTradeReports : Failed to create leg atomic trades for spread product in quote trigger",
7263                                spe);
7264                throw ExceptionBuilder.systemException("createSpreadLegsTradeReports " + spe, 0);
7265            }
7266        }
7267 
7268        aTradeReport.completePendingTrade(atomicTrades, myIdService, buySideLegsMap,
7269                sellSideLegsMap);
7270    }
7271 
7272    /*
7273     * UD 10/07/04 ...Create atomic trades for spread legs participants in quoteTrigger [spread to
7274     * spread]
7275    */
7276    public void createStrategyLegsAtomicTrades(OrderBook book, QuoteTriggerTradable aQuoteTrigger,
7277            ParticipantList buyers, ParticipantList sellers, QuoteTriggerTradeReport aTradeReport,
7278            HashMap buySideLegsMap, HashMap sellSideLegsMap) throws SpreadProcessingException,
7279            DataValidationException, SystemException
7280    {
7281        StrategyLegTradePrice[] legPrices = aTradeReport.getStrategyLegTradePrices();
7282        // Future use, if needed(see comment above in saveLegPricesAtQTCreation())
7283//        TradingProduct[] tradingProducts = aTradeReport.getTradingProductsFromLegTradePrices();
7284        ParticipantList[] bidLists = buyers.getListsForLegs(legPrices, aTradeReport
7285                .getDerivedTradeSide(), null);
7286        ParticipantList[] askLists = sellers.getListsForLegs(legPrices, aTradeReport
7287                .getDerivedTradeSide(), null);
7288        Price[] tradePrices = aTradeReport.getTradePricesOfLegs();
7289        Side[] legSides = aTradeReport.getSidesOfLegs();
7290        for (int i = 0; i < tradePrices.length; i++)
7291        {
7292            ArrayList atomicTrades = new ArrayList();
7293 
7294            if (legSides[i].isBuySide())
7295            {
7296                setContainersForLegSidesMap(buySideLegsMap, sellSideLegsMap, legPrices[i]
7297                        .getTradingProduct(), tradePrices[i], legSides[i], bidLists[i],
7298                        askLists[i], atomicTrades);
7299                // Future use, if needed(see comment above in saveLegPricesAtQTCreation())
7300                // tradingProducts[i], tradePrices[i], legSides[i], bidLists[i], askLists[i],
7301                // atomicTrades);
7302            }
7303            else
7304            {
7305                setContainersForLegSidesMap(buySideLegsMap, sellSideLegsMap, legPrices[i]
7306                        .getTradingProduct(), tradePrices[i], legSides[i], askLists[i],
7307                        bidLists[i], atomicTrades);
7308                // Future use, if needed(see comment above in saveLegPricesAtQTCreation())
7309                // tradingProducts[i], tradePrices[i], legSides[i], askLists[i], bidLists[i],
7310                // atomicTrades);
7311            }
7312        }
7313    }

7315    /*
7316     * UD 10/15/04 Create atomic trades for leg and save buyer/seller leg info in
7317     * buySideMap/sellSideMap.
7318    */
7319    private void setContainersForLegSidesMap(HashMap buySideLegsMap, HashMap sellSideLegsMap,
7320                                      TradingProduct tradingProduct, Price legTradePrice, Side legSide,
7321                                      ParticipantList bidList, ParticipantList askList, ArrayList atomicTrades)
7322        throws DataValidationException
7323    {
7324        StrategyLegQuoteTriggerContainer spreadQTBuySideContainter;
7325        StrategyLegQuoteTriggerContainer spreadQTSellSideContainter;
7326 
7327        int matchQuantity = createAtomicTrades(bidList, askList, atomicTrades, tradingProduct);
7328        // BUGBUG: If split occurs then matchQuantity can not be used instead, tradeQty should be
7329        // used while reporting
7330        spreadQTBuySideContainter = new StrategyLegQuoteTriggerContainer(tradingProduct, bidList,
7331                legTradePrice, legSide, matchQuantity, atomicTrades);

7334                legTradePrice, legSide.getOtherSide(), matchQuantity, atomicTrades);
7335        sellSideLegsMap.put(tradingProduct, spreadQTSellSideContainter);
7336        // Following should be used
7337//        addStrategyLegQuoteTriggerContainerToMap(sellSideLegsMap, spreadQTSellSideContainter);
7338//        addStrategyLegQuoteTriggerContainerToMap(buySideLegsMap, spreadQTBuySideContainter);
7339    }

7341    /*
7342     * 10/07/04 ... Returns legPrices based on buyers and sellers
7343     */
7344    private StrategyLegTradePrice[] getLegPrices(TradingProduct tradingProduct, Price tradePrice,
7345            ParticipantList buyers, ParticipantList sellers, Side derivedTradeSide)
7346        throws SpreadProcessingException, DataValidationException, SystemException
7347    {
7348        StrategyLegTradePrice[] legPrices;
7349        if (buyers.isRegularList() && sellers.isRegularList())
7350        { // spread order trade with spread order
7351            derivedTradeSide = null;    /* value will not be used */
7352            legPrices = calculateTradePricesForLegs(buyers, sellers, tradePrice, tradingProduct, false);
7353        }
7354        else if (buyers.isDerivedList() && sellers.isRegularList())
7355        {
7356            derivedTradeSide = SideFactory.getAsDefinedSide();
7357            legPrices = buyers.getLegTradePrices();
7358        }
7359        else if (buyers.isRegularList() && sellers.isDerivedList())
7360        {
7361            derivedTradeSide = SideFactory.getOppositeSide();
7362            legPrices = sellers.getLegTradePrices();
7363        }
7364        else
7365        {
7366            throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(
7367                    "Unexpected combination of participant list types for trade", 0);
7368        }
7369        return legPrices;
7370    }

7372    /**
7373     * create final participant list for a quote trigger when it expires
7374     */
7375    private int createParticipantListForQuoteTrigger(ParticipantList finalList, OrderBook book,
7376            QuoteTriggerTradable aQuoteTrigger, int quantityToAllocate)
7377    {
7378        int allocatedQuantity = 0;
7379        int size = 0;
7380        Price triggerPrice = aQuoteTrigger.getNonQPrice();
7381        AllocationTradeContext allocationContext = new AllocationTradeContextImpl(
7382                AllocationTradeTypes.QUOTE_TRIGGER);
7383        Iterator sets = book.getPrioritySets(aQuoteTrigger.getPriceDetails(), triggerPrice,
7384                quantityToAllocate, allocationContext);
7385        while (sets.hasNext() && allocatedQuantity < quantityToAllocate)
7386        {
7387            PriorityTradableSet nextSet = (PriorityTradableSet) sets.next();
7388            size = size + 1;
7389            int nextAllocatedQuantity = nextSet.allocate(finalList, quantityToAllocate
7390                    - allocatedQuantity);
7391            allocatedQuantity += nextAllocatedQuantity;
7392            if (Log.isDebugOn() && size > 1)
7393            {
7394                Log
7395                        .debug("TradeServiceImpl >>> OrderBook return more than 1 prioripty set "
7396                                + size);
7397            }
7398        }
7399        return allocatedQuantity;
7400    }

7413    }

7428    protected StrategyLegTradePrice[] calculateTradePricesForFlexStrategyLegs(ParticipantList aBiders,

7437    /**
7438     * calculate leg prices for spread to spread QCT trade.
7439     */
7440    protected StrategyLegTradePrice[] calculateQCTTradePricesForLegs(ParticipantList aBiders,
7441            ParticipantList aAskers, Price aTradePrice, TradingProduct aTradingProduct)
7442            throws DataValidationException, SpreadProcessingException, SystemException
7443    {
7444        HashSet quantities = aBiders.getDistinctParticipantQuantities();
7445        quantities.addAll(aAskers.getDistinctParticipantQuantities());
7446        DerivedQuote derivedQuote = StrategyTradeServiceHelper
7447                .getDerivedQuoteWithNBBO(aTradingProduct);

7449        {
7450            throw new SpreadProcessingException(
7451                    "TradServiceImpl.calculateQCTTradePricesForLegs :Unable to calculate derived quote) >>>",
7452                    SpreadProcessingException.LegPricesCanNotBeCalculated);
7453        }
7454        AllocationContext context = new AllocationContextImpl();
7455        context.setContext(AllocationContext.CURRENT_DQ, derivedQuote);
7456        context.setContext(AllocationContext.TRADE_TYPE, new Integer(AllocationTradeTypes.REGULAR));
7457        context.setContext(AllocationContext.BYPASS_PENNY_BETTER_CHECK, new Boolean("true"));
7458        return StrategyTradeServiceHelper.calculateTradePriceForLegs(aTradingProduct, aTradePrice,
7459                quantities,context);
7460    }

7505    /**
7506     * acceptTradeUpdate - allow SAGUI to modify some clearing information for an active trade
7507     * 
7508     * @param sessionName
7509     * @param productKey
7510     * @param tradeId
7511     * @param atomicTradeStructs
7512     * @throws SystemException
7513     * @throws CommunicationException
7514     * @throws AuthorizationException
7515     * @throws DataValidationException
7516     * @throws NotAcceptedException
7517     * @throws TransactionFailedException
7518     */
7519    public void acceptTradeUpdate(String sessionName, int productKey, CboeIdStruct tradeId,
7520            AtomicTradeStruct[] atomicTradeStructs) throws SystemException, CommunicationException,
7521            AuthorizationException, DataValidationException, NotAcceptedException,
7522            TransactionFailedException
7523    {
7524        String openSessionName = TradingSessionNameHelper.getOpenConfiguredSessionName();
7525        if (sessionName == null || openSessionName == null || !openSessionName.equals(sessionName))
7526        {
7527            String message = "Given session(" + sessionName
7528                    + ") is not the current Open sessionName(" + openSessionName
7529                    + "), in TradeService.acceptTradeUpdate().";
7530            Log.alarm(this, message);
7531            throw ExceptionBuilder.notAcceptedException(message, NotAcceptedCodes.INVALID_STATE);
7532        }
7533 
7534        // validate the trade report Id
7535        TradeReport tradeReport;
7536        try
7537        {
7538            tradeReport = getTradeReport(CboeId.longValue(tradeId));
7539        }
7540        catch (NotFoundException nfe)
7541        {
7542            String msg = "Unable to find trade report for tradeId ( " + tradeId + "), "
7543                    + nfe.details.message;
7544            Log.exception(this, msg, nfe);
7545            throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(msg, 0);
7546        }
7547 
7548        if(tradeReport.getTradeType() == TradeTypes.HANDHELD_TRADE)
7549        {
7550            String msg = "Trade (" + tradeId + ") is an MMHH-MMHH Trade so it can't be modified.";
7551            Log.alarm(this, msg);
7552            throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(msg,
7553            DataValidationCodes.INVALID_TRADE_TYPE);
7554        }
7555 
7556        // to check if this trade Report is part of the Strategy Trade Reports
7557        if (tradeReport.isStrategyReport())
7558        {
7559            String msg = "Trade (" + tradeId
7560                    + ") is not able to modified, it is part of Strategy Trade Reports";
7561            Log.alarm(this, msg);
7562            throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(msg,
7563                    DataValidationCodes.INVALID_UPDATE_ATTEMPT);
7564        }
7565 
7566        // validate product Key
7567        TradingProduct tradingProduct = null;
7568        try
7569        {
7570            tradingProduct = getTradingProductHome().findByKey(productKey);
7571        }
7572        catch (NotFoundException e)
7573        {
7574            String message = "Given ProductKey (" + productKey + ") cannot be found in session ("
7575                    + sessionName + ")!";
7576            Log.exception(this, message, e);
7577            throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(message,
7578                    DataValidationCodes.INVALID_PRODUCT);
7579        }
7580 
7581        int productType = tradingProduct.getProductKeys().productType;
7582 
7583        if (tradingProduct.getProductKeys().productType == ProductTypes.STRATEGY)
7584        {
7585            Log.alarm("Update trade for strategy products are not accepted");
7586            throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(
7587                    "Update trade for strategy products are not accepted",
7588                    DataValidationCodes.INVALID_PRODUCT_TYPE);
7589        }

7591        TradeValidationStrategy strategy = getTradeValidationStrategy(sessionName, productType);
7592        // validate the update trade request
7593        validateUpdateTrade(tradeReport, atomicTradeStructs, strategy);
7594 
7595        try
7596        {
7597            // execute within product lock, else delegate to class lock:
7598            tradingProduct.acceptCommand(new AcceptTradeUpdateCommand(CboeId.longValue(tradeId),
7599                    atomicTradeStructs, strategy), false);
7600        }
7601        catch (NotAcceptedException e2)
7602        {
7603            Log.exception(this, "Request not accepted by broker " + e2.details.message, e2);
7604            throw e2;
7605        }
7606    }

7608    /**
7609     * Once a AcceptTradeUpdate is dequeued from the TradingClass, this method is invoked to
7610     * complete processing the update request in sequence.
7611     * 
7612     * @param tradeId
7613     * @param tradesToUpdate
7614     **/
7615    public void processTradeUpdate(long tradeId, AtomicTradeStruct[] tradesToUpdate,
7616            TradeValidationStrategy strategy) throws SystemException, CommunicationException,
7617            AuthorizationException, DataValidationException, NotAcceptedException,
7618            TransactionFailedException
7619    {
7620        TradeReport tradeReport;
7621        try
7622        {
7623            tradeReport = getTradeReport(tradeId);
7624        }
7625        catch (NotFoundException nfe)
7626        {
7627            String msg = "Unable to find trade report for tradeId ( " + tradeId + "), "
7628                    + nfe.details.message;
7629            Log.exception(this, msg, nfe);
7630            throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(msg, 0);
7631        }
7632 
7633        // validate the update trade request
7634        validateUpdateTrade(tradeReport, tradesToUpdate, strategy);
7635 
7636        // the update logic of tradeReport
7637        tradeReport.update(tradesToUpdate, myIdService);
7638}
7639 
7640    // validate the update trade request
7641    protected void validateUpdateTrade(TradeReport tradeReport,
7642            AtomicTradeStruct[] atomicTradeStructs, TradeValidationStrategy strategy)
7643            throws DataValidationException, AuthorizationException, CommunicationException,
7644            SystemException
7645{
7646    // verify that each atomic trade can be found and active
7647    for (int i = 0; i < atomicTradeStructs.length; ++i)
7648    {
7649        // Get affected entry and verify id - DataValidation will be thrown if entry not found
7650            TradeReportEntry affectedEntry = tradeReport.findTradeReportEntry(CboeId
7651                    .longValue(atomicTradeStructs[i].atomicTradeId));
7652 
7653            // Can only modify it if entry is active and entry type and last entry type are both ADD
7654            // entries
7655            if (!affectedEntry.isActive()
7656                    || (affectedEntry.getEntryType() != TradeReportEntryTypes.ADD)
7657                    || (affectedEntry.getLastEntryType() != TradeReportEntryTypes.ADD))
7658        {
7659            String message = "Cannot modify an inactive or deleted trade.";
7660            Log.alarm(this, message);
7661                throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(message,
7662                        DataValidationCodes.INVALID_UPDATE_ATTEMPT);
7663        }
7664 
7665        try
7666        {
7667            // validate the trade the update fields from update request
7668            strategy.validateUpdateTrade(affectedEntry, atomicTradeStructs[i]);
7669        }
7670        catch (DataValidationException e)
7671        {
7672            Log.exception(this, e.details.message, e);
7673            throw e;
7674        }
7675    }
7676}

7678    /**
7679     * Create a trade between the incomind quote and booked Q-tradables only, and each of the booked
7680     * Q-tradables can be only traded the Minimum Quote Lock Quantity at most.
7681     */
7682    public int createQuoteLockMinTrade(Tradable tradable, TradingProduct aProduct, OrderBook book,
7683            Price expectedEndingTradePrice) throws SpreadProcessingException,
7684            DataValidationException, SystemException
7685    {
7686        int allocatedQuantity = 0;
7687        Side otherSide = tradable.getSide().getOtherSide();
7688        int quantityToAllocate = tradable.getQuantityAllowed();
7689        ArrayList oppositeParticipantLists = new ArrayList();
7690        ArrayList tradePrices = new ArrayList();
7691        ArrayList tradeQuantities = new ArrayList();
7692        
7693        int oppositeAllocatedQuantity = createParticipantListsOfQuoteLockMinTrade(
7694                oppositeParticipantLists, tradePrices, tradeQuantities, aProduct, book, otherSide,
7695                expectedEndingTradePrice, quantityToAllocate);
7696        if (oppositeAllocatedQuantity > 0)
7697        {

7699            int sameSideAllocatedQuantity = createParticipantLists(incomingParticipantLists,
7700                    tradePrices, tradeQuantities, tradable, null, oppositeAllocatedQuantity,
7701                    aProduct.getTradingClass());
7702            if (sameSideAllocatedQuantity != oppositeAllocatedQuantity)
7703            {
7704                allocatedQuantity = 0;
7705            }
7706            else
7707            {
7708                allocatedQuantity = sameSideAllocatedQuantity;
7709                Side updatedSide = otherSide;
7710                Tradable unBookedTradable = tradable;
7711                if (otherSide.isBuySide() || otherSide.isAsDefinedSide())
7712                {
7713                    completeTrades(unBookedTradable, oppositeParticipantLists,
7714                            incomingParticipantLists, tradePrices, tradeQuantities, book,
7715                            updatedSide);
7716                }
7717                else
7718                {
7719                    completeTrades(unBookedTradable, incomingParticipantLists,
7720                            oppositeParticipantLists, tradePrices, tradeQuantities, book,
7721                            updatedSide);
7722                }
7723            } // end else
7724        }
7725 
7726        return allocatedQuantity;
7727    }

7776 
7777    public int createInternalizationTrade(InternalizationPair internalizationPair, OrderBook book,
7778            Price tradePrice) throws SystemException
7779    {
7780        Side otherSide = internalizationPair.getPrimaryOrder().getSide().getOtherSide();
7781        // try to trade @ best book price or 1-tick better than best book of the internalized order
7782        // side
7783        int incomingRemainingQty = 0; // since in this case, there will be no qty left and could
7784                                      // trade with customer qty of the book
7785        int allocatedQuantity = 0;
7786        if (tradePrice == null)
7787        {
7788            // if tradePrice is not given, use top BBO or 1 tick better than top BBO if there's cust
7789            // vol. on top BBO
7790            tradePrice = AuctionTradeHelper.getBestBookPriceOrOneTickBetter(otherSide
7791                    .getOtherSide(), book, AuctionTypes.AUCTION_INTERNALIZATION,
7792                    incomingRemainingQty);
7793            // for Cust-cust AIM, need to re-check the ajusted price against the opposite site NBBO
7794            if (canNotTradeInternally(internalizationPair, book, tradePrice, otherSide))
7795            {
7796                return allocatedQuantity; // no trade, both orders will be cancelled/rerouted
7797            }
7798        }
7799 
7800        if (!(internalizationPair.getSecondaryOrder().getSide().isFirstBetterOrEqual(
7801                internalizationPair.getSecondaryOrder().getPrice(), tradePrice) && internalizationPair
7802                .getPrimaryOrder().getSide().isFirstBetterOrEqual(
7803                        internalizationPair.getPrimaryOrder().getPrice(), tradePrice)))
7804        {
7805            Log.alarm(this, this.getClass().getName()
7806                    + ".createInternalizationTrade => the allocated quantity is 0");
7807            return allocatedQuantity; // couldn't trade at the given trade price
7808        }
7809        int quantityToAllocate = internalizationPair.getPrimaryOrder().getQuantityAllowed();
7810        ArrayList oppositeParticipantLists = new ArrayList();
7811        ArrayList tradePrices = new ArrayList();
7812        ArrayList tradeQuantities = new ArrayList();
7813        
7814        int oppositeAllocatedQuantity = AuctionTradeHelper.createInternalizationParticipantLists(
7815                internalizationPair, oppositeParticipantLists, tradePrices, tradeQuantities, book,
7816                tradePrice, quantityToAllocate);
7817        if (oppositeAllocatedQuantity > 0)
7818        {
7819            ArrayList incomingParticipantLists = new ArrayList();
7820 
7821            int sameSideAllocatedQuantity = createParticipantLists(incomingParticipantLists,
7822                    tradePrices, tradeQuantities, internalizationPair.getPrimaryOrder(), null,
7823                    oppositeAllocatedQuantity, book.getTradingProduct().getTradingClass());
7824 
7825            AuctionTradeHelper.prepareParticipantsForTrade(oppositeParticipantLists,
7826                    TradeContext.AUCTION_TRADE);
7827            AuctionTradeHelper.prepareParticipantsForTrade(incomingParticipantLists,
7828                    TradeContext.AUCTION_TRADE);
7829 
7830            if (sameSideAllocatedQuantity != oppositeAllocatedQuantity)
7831            {
7832                allocatedQuantity = 0;
7833                Log.alarm(this, this.getClass().getName()
7834                        + ".createInternalizationTrade => the allocated quantity("
7835                        + sameSideAllocatedQuantity + ") is different from the other side ( "
7836                        + oppositeAllocatedQuantity + ")");
7837            }
7838            else
7839            {
7840                allocatedQuantity = sameSideAllocatedQuantity;
7841                Side updatedSide = otherSide;
7842                try
7843                {
7844                    if (otherSide.isBuySide())
7845                    {
7846                        completeTrades(null, oppositeParticipantLists, incomingParticipantLists,
7847                                tradePrices, tradeQuantities, book, updatedSide);
7848                    }
7849                    else
7850                    {
7851                        completeTrades(null, incomingParticipantLists, oppositeParticipantLists,
7852                                tradePrices, tradeQuantities, book, updatedSide);
7853                    }
7854                }
7855                catch (SpreadProcessingException spe)
7856                {
7857                    Log.exception(this, spe);
7858                    throw ExceptionBuilder.systemException(spe.getMessage(),  0);
7859                }
7860                catch (DataValidationException de)
7861                {
7862                    Log.exception(this, de);
7863                    throw ExceptionBuilder.systemException(de.getMessage(),  0);
7864                }
7865            } // end else
7866        }
7867 
7868        return  allocatedQuantity;
7869    }
7870 
7871    /**
7872     * check whether it can trade internally or not.
7873     * 
7874     * @param internalizationPair
7875     * @param book
7876     * @param tradePrice
7877     * @param otherSide
7878     * @return true, if the trade price will not trade through the opposite NBBO/top customer price,
7879     *         otherwise, if the trade price is out of the range, then return true
7880     */
7881    private boolean canNotTradeInternally(InternalizationPair internalizationPair, OrderBook book,
7882            Price tradePrice, Side otherSide)
7883    {
7884        if (!AuctionProcessorBase.isCust2CustAIM(internalizationPair))
7885        {
7886            return false; // as this rule only applies to AIM Cust-cust
7887        }
7888        if(internalizationPair.isISO())
7889        {
7890            return false; // as AIM ISO ignores NBBO
7891        }   
7892        boolean notTrade = false;
7893        String message = "";
7894        Price auctionOppositeSideNBBO = internalizationPair.getNBBOPrice(true);
7895        if (otherSide.isFirstBetter(auctionOppositeSideNBBO, tradePrice))
7896        {
7897            notTrade = true;
7898            message = "Due to potential trade price=" + tradePrice + " worse than opposite NBBO="
7899                    + auctionOppositeSideNBBO;
7900        }
7901        else if (OrderBookImpl.isWorseThanBBOorEqualToCustomer(tradePrice, otherSide, book))
7902        {
7903            notTrade = true;
7904            message = "Due to potential trade price=" + tradePrice
7905                    + " worse than or equal to opposite BBO.";
7906        }
7907        if (notTrade)
7908        {
7909            message = "Cust-Cust AIM won't trade internally between primary Order( "
7910                + StructToString.toString(internalizationPair.getPrimaryOrder().getOrderId())
7911                + ") and match Order ( "
7912                + StructToString.toString(internalizationPair.getSecondaryOrder().getOrderId())
7913                + ")," + message;
7914            Log.information(this, message);
7915        }
7916        return notTrade;
7917    }
7918 
7919    /**
7920      * Gets next tradable starting from the current tradable passed in.
7921      */
7922    private Tradable getNextTradableFromCurrent(Tradable currentTradable,
7923            Enumeration theSideMarkets, Tradable firstTradable, int quantityRemaining,
7924            TradingClass tradingClass)
7925         {
7926        if (currentTradable == null)
7927        {
7928            if (firstTradable != null
7929                    && getMinQuantity(tradingClass, firstTradable) <= quantityRemaining)
7930             {
7931                 return firstTradable;
7932             }
7933         }
7934        while (theSideMarkets != null && theSideMarkets.hasMoreElements())
7935        {
7936             Tradable nextTradable = (Tradable) theSideMarkets.nextElement();
7937             if (getMinQuantity(tradingClass, nextTradable) <= quantityRemaining)
7938             {
7939                 return nextTradable;
7940             }
7941         }
7942         return null;
7943     }

8140    /**
8141     * Tells whether or not an entry that associates userAcronym and p_userId exists in a given look
8142     * up source. The look up is based on a key which is made up of a combination of the passed
8143     * parameters. The actual look up is performed by FirmPropertyService since it occurs on a table
8144     * created with user properties. The initial goal of this method is to provide with an
8145     * alternative look up method (user id - acronym) in additon to just looking at the acronym
8146     * field inside a UserStruct.
8147     *

8149     * @param classKey
8150     * @param userAcronym. the acronym.
8151     * @param p_userId: the user id.
8152     * @return true if a match is found, false otherwise.
8153     * 
8154     * @autor Francisco Ojeda
8155     */        
8156    private boolean associationFound(String sessionName, String firmNumber, String exchange,
8157            int classKey, String userAcronym, String userId)
8158    {
8159        boolean relationFound = false;
8160         
8161        BasePropertyKey key = buildSessionFirmClassAcronymKey(sessionName, firmNumber, exchange,
8162                userAcronym, classKey);
8163        
8164        String cmiUser = getFirmPropertyService().getMMTNCmiUser(key);
8165        if(cmiUser != null && userId.compareTo(cmiUser.trim()) == 0) 
8166        {
8167            relationFound = true;
8168        }
8169        return relationFound;
8170    }
8171    
8172    /**
8173     * Fills in certain fields (executing firm, account & subaccount) of p_TradeEntry using the 
8174     * information found in userInfo. The initial goal of this method is to use the values from user
8175     * info (overwriting the parameters passed in the original FloorTradeEntryStruct).
8176     * 
8177     * @param p_TradeEntry: floor trade which fields will be filled in.
8178     * @param userInfo: UserStruct from where the information to fill in the empty fiels will be
8179     * obtained.
8180     * @param classKey: the class key of the product being traded.
8181     * @return FloorTradeEntryStruct: this object is very similar to the p_TradeEntry argument, the
8182     * difference is in the firm, account and subaccount fields.
8183     * 
8184     * @autor Francisco Ojeda
8185     */    
8186    private FloorTradeEntryStruct fillWithUserInfo(FloorTradeEntryStruct p_TradeEntry,
8187            SessionProfileUserStruct sessionProfileUserStruct, int classKey)
8188    {
8189        boolean useUserProvidedAccount = false;
8190        boolean useUserProvidedSubaccount = false;
8191        String accMsg = "";
8192        String subaccMsg = "";
8193 
8194        // Overwrites the executing firm passed in the trade with the firm in user struct.  
8195        p_TradeEntry.firm = sessionProfileUserStruct.firm;
8196        
8197        if (p_TradeEntry.account != null && p_TradeEntry.account.length() > 0)
8198        {
8199            useUserProvidedAccount = true;
8200            accMsg = "Using user provided account value (" + p_TradeEntry.account + ").";
8201        }
8202 
8203        if (p_TradeEntry.subaccount != null && p_TradeEntry.subaccount.length() > 0)
8204        {
8205            useUserProvidedSubaccount = true;
8206            subaccMsg = "Using user provided subaccount value (" + p_TradeEntry.subaccount + ").";
8207        }
8208 
8209        // If account and subacount are provided by user in p_TradeEntry we keep these values.
8210        if (useUserProvidedAccount && useUserProvidedSubaccount)
8211        {
8212            String message = "In class " + this.getClass().getName()
8213                    + ".fillWithUserInfo() using user id: " + sessionProfileUserStruct.userId
8214                    + " found user provided information. " + accMsg + subaccMsg;
8215            Log.information(this, message);
8216            return p_TradeEntry;
8217        }
8218 
8219        // Look up the passed class in user struct's sessionProfilesByClass to obtain the account
8220        // and subaccount from class specific session profile.
8221        for ( int i = 0; i < sessionProfileUserStruct.sessionProfilesByClass.length; i++ )    
8222        {
8223            if (sessionProfileUserStruct.sessionProfilesByClass[i].sessionName
8224                    .equals(p_TradeEntry.sessionName)
8225                    && sessionProfileUserStruct.sessionProfilesByClass[i].classKey == classKey)
8226            {
8227                if (!useUserProvidedAccount)
8228            {
8229                p_TradeEntry.account = sessionProfileUserStruct.sessionProfilesByClass[i].account;
8230                    accMsg = "Using account value (" + p_TradeEntry.account + ") from profile. ";
8231                }
8232 
8233                if (!useUserProvidedSubaccount)
8234                {
8235                p_TradeEntry.subaccount = sessionProfileUserStruct.sessionProfilesByClass[i].subAccount;
8236                    subaccMsg = "Using subaccount value (" + p_TradeEntry.subaccount + ") from profile. ";
8237                }
8238 
8239                String message = "In class " + this.getClass().getName()
8240                        + ".fillWithUserInfo() using user id: " + sessionProfileUserStruct.userId
8241                        + " found class specific profile for session: " + p_TradeEntry.sessionName
8242                        + ", classKey: " + classKey + " in user's session profiles by class. "
8243                        + accMsg + subaccMsg;
8244                Log.information(this, message);
8245 
8246                return p_TradeEntry;
8247            }
8248        }
8249 
8250        // If no matches found in sessionProfilesByClass try to find a session default profile to
8251        // obtain account and subaccount from.
8252        for ( int i = 0; i < sessionProfileUserStruct.defaultSessionProfiles.length; i++)    
8253        {
8254            if (sessionProfileUserStruct.defaultSessionProfiles[i].sessionName
8255                    .equals(p_TradeEntry.sessionName))
8256            {
8257                if (!useUserProvidedAccount)
8258            {
8259                p_TradeEntry.account = sessionProfileUserStruct.defaultSessionProfiles[i].account;
8260                    accMsg = "Using account value (" + p_TradeEntry.account + ") from profile. ";
8261                }
8262 
8263                if (!useUserProvidedSubaccount)
8264                {
8265                p_TradeEntry.subaccount = sessionProfileUserStruct.defaultSessionProfiles[i].subAccount;
8266                    subaccMsg = "Using subaccount value (" + p_TradeEntry.subaccount + ") from profile. ";
8267                }
8268 
8269                String message = "In class " + this.getClass().getName()
8270                        + ".fillWithUserInfo() using user id: " + sessionProfileUserStruct.userId
8271                        + " found a default profile for session: " + p_TradeEntry.sessionName
8272                        + " in user's default session profiles. " + accMsg + subaccMsg;
8273                Log.information(this, message); 
8274                
8275                return p_TradeEntry;
8276            }            
8277        }        
8278        
8279        // If no session default profile then use the user default profile.
8280        if (!useUserProvidedAccount)
8281        {
8282        p_TradeEntry.account = sessionProfileUserStruct.defaultProfile.account;
8283            accMsg = "Using account value (" + p_TradeEntry.account + ") from profile. ";
8284        }
8285 
8286        if (!useUserProvidedSubaccount)
8287        {
8288        p_TradeEntry.subaccount = sessionProfileUserStruct.defaultProfile.subAccount;
8289            subaccMsg = "Using subaccount value (" + p_TradeEntry.subaccount + ") from profile. ";
8290        }
8291 
8292        String message = "In class " + this.getClass().getName()
8293                + ".fillWithUserInfo() using user id: " + sessionProfileUserStruct.userId
8294                + " could not find exact profile match for session: " + p_TradeEntry.sessionName
8295                + ", classKey: " + classKey + " in user's session profiles by class. "
8296                + "Could not find a default profile for session: " + p_TradeEntry.sessionName
8297                + " in user's default session profiles. Default user profile will be used. " + accMsg
8298                + subaccMsg;
8299        Log.information(this, message);
8300        
8301        return p_TradeEntry;
8302    }

8347    /**
8348     * Working method to accept and process floor trades. The goal of this method is to support 
8349     * handheld trades processing inside the trade service. Handheld trades have their two sides 
8350     * with different amount of information. This is, one side always contains more information than
8351     * the other. They require a fair amount of validation and "filling-the-balnks" before the
8352     * actual trade could be executed. This method takes care of these two tasks: validation and
8353     * infromation completion. Currenlty Handheld trades are accepted in W_MAIN session only.
8354     * 
8355     * @param p_tradeEntryStruct: floor trade.
8356     * @param userId: id of user sending the trade.
8357     * @param tradeType: type of floor trade. Currenlty only handheld trades are allowed.
8358     * @return CboeIdStruct corresponding to the accepted trade id.
8359     * @throws SystemException
8360     * @throws CommunicationException
8361     * @throws AuthorizationException
8362     * @throws DataValidationException
8363     * @throws NotAcceptedException
8364     * @throws TransactionFailedException
8365     * 
8366     * @autor Francisco Ojeda
8367     */    
8368    
8369    private CboeIdStruct processFloorTradeRequest(FloorTradeEntryStruct p_tradeEntryStruct,
8370            String p_userId, char p_tradeType) throws SystemException, CommunicationException,
8371            AuthorizationException, DataValidationException, NotAcceptedException,
8372            TransactionFailedException
8373    {

8378        Log.debug(this, message0 + ", " +  floorTradeStructToString(p_tradeEntryStruct));

8382        TradingProduct product = getTradingProduct(p_tradeEntryStruct.productKey);

8393

8395            {
8396                Log.debug(this, message);
8397            }
8398            
8399            throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(message,
8400                    DataValidationCodes.INVALID_PRODUCT);
8401        }

8403        
8404        if (classKey <= 0) 
8405        {
8406            String message = "Invalid product class. Product with key: "
8407                    + p_tradeEntryStruct.productKey
8408                    + " corresponds to a class with an invalid class key: "

8420        // trade report.

8425 
8426        // FIRST LOOKUP: lookup user by userId and match the user's acronym with the passed acronym.
8427 
8428        // Get user from UserService using passed userId.
8429        try
8430        {

8432        }
8433        catch (NotFoundException e)
8434        {

8436                    + " . Could not find a user that matches this id. ";
8437            Log.information(this, message);
8438        }
8439        
8440        // Match passed acronym and acronym of user returned from UserService.
8441        ExchangeAcronymContainer acronymFromPassedIdContainer = new ExchangeAcronymContainer(
8442                userFromPassedId.userAcronym);
8443        ExchangeAcronymContainer passedAcronymContainer = new ExchangeAcronymContainer(
8444                p_tradeEntryStruct.executingMarketMaker);
8445 
8446        if (!acronymFromPassedIdContainer.equalsIgnoringExchange(passedAcronymContainer))
8447        {

8449                    + p_tradeEntryStruct.executingMarketMaker.acronym

8451                    + p_userId;
8452            Log.information(this, message);
8453 
8454            // SECOND LOOKUP: match userId and passed acronym. If match exist use passed acronym to
8455            // get user.
8456

8458            try
8459            {

8461                        p_tradeEntryStruct.executingMarketMaker);

8463            catch (NotFoundException e)
8464            {
8465                String message1 = "Invalid executig acronym: " + passedAcronymContainer
8466                        + " . UserService could not find a user that matches this acronym. ";

8468                        DataValidationCodes.INVALID_USER);
8469            }        
8470 
8471            // Match passed userId and acronym using property lookup.
8472            if (!associationFound(p_tradeEntryStruct.sessionName,
8473                    userFromPassedAcronym.firm.firmNumber, userFromPassedAcronym.firm.exchange,
8474                    classKey, p_tradeEntryStruct.executingMarketMaker.acronym, p_userId))

8480                throw ExceptionBuilder.notAcceptedException(message2,
8481                        NotAcceptedCodes.INVALID_REQUEST);
8482            }   
8483            else
8484            {

8486                String message3 = "Found relation executing acronym - userId ( "

8488                        + " ) in firm properties. ";
8489                Log.information(this, message3);
8490           }
8491        }
8492        else
8493        {
8494            executingUser = userFromPassedId;
8495            String message4 = "Found relation userId - executing acronym ( " + p_userId + " - "
8496                    + p_tradeEntryStruct.executingMarketMaker.acronym + " ) in user cache. ";
8497            Log.information(this, message4);
8498        }
8499 
8500        // Executing side must be a market maker.
8501        if (executingUser.role != UserRoles.MARKET_MAKER
8502                && executingUser.role != UserRoles.DPM_ROLE)
8503        {
8504            String message = "Invalid executing user role: "
8505                    + executingUser.role
8506                    + ". In a HANDHELD_TRADE the excecuting user must be on MARKET_MAKER (M) or DPM_ROLE (D) role. ";
8507 
8508            throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(message,
8509                    DataValidationCodes.INVALID_USER);

8513        FloorTradeEntryStruct modifiedTradeEntryStruct = fillWithUserInfo(p_tradeEntryStruct,
8514                executingUser, classKey);
8515        if(Log.isDebugOn())

8531    private void testARException(TradeReportStruct externalTrade, char tradedSide)
8532            throws SystemException, CommunicationException, DataValidationException,
8533    TransactionFailedException, AuthorizationException
8534    {
8535        String branch;
8536        if (tradedSide == Sides.BUY)
8537        {
8538            branch = externalTrade.parties[0].buyerFirmBranch;
8539        }
8540        else
8541        {
8542            branch = externalTrade.parties[0].sellerFirmBranch;
8543        }
8544 
8545        if (exceptionTypeAR != null && orderBranchAR != null && orderBranchAR.equals(branch))
8546        {
8547            if (exceptionTypeAR.equals("SE"))
8548            {
8549                throw ExceptionBuilder.systemException("testing AR command SystemException", 0);
8550            }
8551            else if (exceptionTypeAR.equals("CE"))
8552            {
8553                throw ExceptionBuilder.communicationException(
8554                        "testing AR command CommunicationException", 0);
8555            }
8556            else if (exceptionTypeAR.equals("TFE"))
8557            {
8558                throw ExceptionBuilder.transactionFailedException(
8559                        "testing AR command TransactionFailedException", 0);
8560            }
8561            else if (exceptionTypeAR.equals("DVE"))
8562            {
8563                throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(
8564                        "testing AR command DataValidationException", 0);
8565            }
8566            else if (exceptionTypeAR.equals("AE"))
8567            {
8568                throw ExceptionBuilder.authorizationException(
8569                        "testing AR command AuthorizationException", 0);
8570            }
8571            else if (exceptionTypeAR.equals("NP"))
8572            {
8573                throw new NullPointerException("testing AR command NullPointerException");
8574            }
8575            else
8576            {
8577                exceptionTypeAR = null;
8578    }
8579        }
8580    }

8647    public TradeReportStructV2 acceptCrossProductLegTrade(String originatingSessionName,
8648            TradeReportStructV2 trade, AtomicTradeBillingStruct[] billings) throws SystemException,
8649            CommunicationException, AuthorizationException, DataValidationException,
8650            NotAcceptedException, TransactionFailedException
8651    {
8652        // check the leg trade price against BBO market for AIM auction
8653        checkBBOForAIMCrossProductTrade(trade);        
8654        trade.settlementTradeReport.settlementDate = EquitySettlementDaysAheadCalculator
8655                .calculateSettlementTradeDate(trade.tradeReport.tradeType);
8656        // if settlement transaction time is 0, set to current date time
8657        if (trade.settlementTradeReport.transactionTime.date.year == 0)
8658        {
8659            trade.settlementTradeReport.transactionTime = (new DateWrapper(new Date()))
8660                    .toDateTimeStruct();
8661        }
8662        // if timeTraded is 0, set to current date time
8663        if (trade.tradeReport.timeTraded.date.year == 0)
8664        {
8665            trade.tradeReport.timeTraded = (new DateWrapper(new Date())).toDateTimeStruct();
8666        }
8667        return this.acceptTradeV2FromStruct(trade, originatingSessionName,
8668                TradeReportHandlingInstructions.REGULAR, billings);
8669    }
8670 
8671    /**
8672     * checkBBOForAIMCrossProductTrade Check the leg trade price against BBO market for AIM auction
8673     * 
8674     * @param trade
8675     * @throws DataValidationException
8676     */
8677    private void checkBBOForAIMCrossProductTrade(TradeReportStructV2 trade)
8678            throws DataValidationException
8679    {
8680              
8681        if (trade.tradeReport.tradeType == TradeTypes.CROSS_PRODUCT_AIM_CROSS_TRADE)
8682        {
8683           // check the leg trade price against BBO market for AIM auction
8684           Price tradePrice = PriceFactory.createValuedPrice(trade.tradeReport.price);
8685           int productKey = trade.tradeReport.productKey;           
8686           OrderBookImpl myOrderBook = (OrderBookImpl) getOrderBookHome().find(productKey);
8687           Side theSide = buySide;           
8688           if (OrderBookImpl.isWorseThanBBOorEqualToCustomer(tradePrice, theSide, myOrderBook))
8689           {                                
8690                handleBBOViolate(tradePrice, productKey, theSide);
8691           }
8692           else
8693           {
8694               theSide = theSide.getOtherSide();
8695               if (OrderBookImpl.isWorseThanBBOorEqualToCustomer(tradePrice, theSide, myOrderBook))
8696               {
8697                    handleBBOViolate(tradePrice, productKey, theSide);
8698               }              
8699           }            
8700        }
8701    }
8702 
8703    private void handleBBOViolate(Price tradePrice, int productKey, Side theSide)
8704            throws DataValidationException
8705    {
8706        ExceptionDetails detail = new ExceptionDetails();
8707        detail.message = "The trade price =" + tradePrice
8708                + "Worse than BBO or same as Customer price of product" + productKey + " on Side: "
8709                + theSide;
8710           Log.alarm(this, detail.message);
8711           throw new DataValidationException(detail);
8712    }

8714    public void completeTradeReport(TradeReport tradeReportToComplete, boolean heldOrderTrade,
8715            ParticipantList biders, ParticipantList askers, Price price, boolean isAsynchronousTrade, Map<Tradable, TradableSnapShot> participantFills)
8716            throws DataValidationException, SystemException
8717    {
8718        doTradeMatch((TradeReportImpl) tradeReportToComplete, tradeReportToComplete
8719                .getTradingProduct(), TradeTypes.CROSS_PRODUCT_LEG_TRADE,
8720                TradeTypes.CROSS_PRODUCT_LEG_TRADE, heldOrderTrade, biders, askers, price,
8721                (TradeReport) null, isAsynchronousTrade, participantFills, new HashMap());
8722
